We are a happy family of 6, 2 adults (in age, not in being) and 4 children, ages 7-13.

We are English, were born in the UK, but have been in living in Australia for 16 years. Prior to settling here, we travelled extensively round the globe for work and play, and love experiencing different countries, people and cultures. We want to share with our children, the beauty of our global community, by opening our home to like minded people from all round the world. 

We have a 2BD quiet unit for peaceful travelers to call home for their stay. This is my parents home, as they ‘chase the sun’ and enjoy family on both sides of the world. 
 
We are soon to put our whole house  under a separate listing for another like minded family to enjoy.

Our family motto is "Do it with passion, or not at all".  
There is never peace and quiet here, but there is always lots of fun!

space: Welcome to St Kilda and to our unique St Kilda mansion. Our five-bedroom house is truly beautiful and in a stunning location. The house is huge (over 400sqm) and is bright, light and airy with heaps of space for up to 10 people to enjoy. This is one of the best locations in St Kilda. You won't need a car (though we have off-street parking for two cars if you do drive). Acland Street is 2-3 minutes walk and the beach about 1km away, Fitzroy Street and Carlisle Street are an easy walk. The St Kilda Botanic Gardens are at our back door and trams to the city (no.96 and 16) within minutes. The house has everything you will need for a short or long term stay, making it perfect for families, groups, girlfriend getaways and corporate relocations. Naturally, there is WiFi and Netflix. Our guests have loved the house's size, the "wow" factor when entering for the first time and the surprisingly peaceful and luxuriously large rear garden. There is a floor plan in the photos. BEDROOMS & BATHROOMS
host_about: From Melbourne, love travelling and eating! host_about:
~ Melbourne sky Apartments~
Dear guests:

We are Eden Charmmy and Cony. We are professional management team . 

All our apartments are unique, therefore we do not offer early check in or late check out  as my apartments are unique, we cannot just put guests in a random available room. 

My team members can speak English Korean Indonesian and Chinese . Pls feel free to contact us anytime. Thank you 
我們可以講中文 
Our working hour is from 10AM TO 10PM. 
We always answer your question within 2 hours during our business hours. 

Important information:

* We provide car park for $15 per 24 hours  ( Multi-entry) . The car park is provided by third party, you will be given an allocated car park number a day before you arrive. 

* There are few car rental companies nearby. You can search car rentals in Southern cross station to save the parking fee if you only need car for few hours.

* We are airbnb not hotel. ( Means you are staying in host's house not a hotel).
Therefore, we do not provide daily cleaning service. Additional cleaning service can be provided at extra cost. 


* Please take your personal belongings with you when you check out. We are not responsible for any lost or damage to your personal belongings.

The building also comes with great common facilities including a pool, gym, common guest/social lounge,BBQ facility, a sauna and a Rock Climbing Wall!  Also has restaurants and cafes on-site too
space: The WHOLE apartment ALL TO YOURSELF directly across Southern Cross Station (Main train station and transport hub) making this efficiently designed, inner-city place ideal for weekenders, business travellers or holiday goers.  My place is comfy and furnished with everyday use amenities, and the building has a pool, gym, sauna, BBQ area, visitor sitting lounge, and also a rock climbing wall! Roomy and comfy for 1 or 2, just nice for 3, accommodates a maximum of 4.  Inside the apartment  is modern, nice and comfy. It has a open plan living area including the lounge with a full kitchen, a sleeping loft, dinning area, laundry facilities and a functional shower room.  I have a full size double bed in my apartment for the first 2 guests and a sofa bed which pulls out into another double size bed for 2 more guests (3rd and 4th guests), convenient for those who are travelling on a budget. Else the sofa bed can fit your kids nicely and they may love the novelty of sleeping on a pull out bed :-)

space: Right in the heart of "Little Italy" in Catlton. Minutes to Melbourne CBD. You are minutes from everything you will need to enjoy this fantastic city. Cafés, restaurants, trams and trains are close. If you want to have easy access to Melbourne and the coolest inner city suburbs. Carlton is the perfect base. This is a great flat to stay in.  Secure Apartment in Carlton. You have access to the entire flat. Comfy bed. Flat screen TV. Modern kitchen stocked with some basics. Wifi throughout the house. Clean bathroom. No Smoking.   Carlton has everything you need and is a great place to see the real Melbourne. We love living here. There are so many cafés and great restaurants you'll be spoilt for choice. We can give you recommendations if you need.  The main tram lines in Melbourne are one block away on Swanston st. Trains are 5 minute walk away at Melbourne Central Station. Best of all though you can walk into the city in 10 minutes! Secure Car parking in the building can be made available
host_about: I initially used Airbnb for our home when we were away ourselves and found it such a great platform that when my rental property became available, I furnished it and put it on Airbnb too. It's been interesting meeting people from all over and I really enjoy trying to get things right to make guests comfortable. Our properties are in two of the most desirable locations on Melbourne; Carlton near the city and Melbourne Uni and St Kilda in the heart of buzzing Acland St, across the road from the beach. I believe we can cater for many different tastes. It's often the little things people remember and it's these details which really make all the difference.

Feel free to contact me if you have pets, but keep in mind that animals here are as plentiful as the Mountain Ash. Aside from the locals, Forrest Retreat is also home to Max the cat, Barry the sheep and a handful of clucky chickens, who don't mind giving their eggs up for a farm fresh omelet for breakfast.

name: Eporo Blush - Modern 2 Bdrm Apt in the CBD
summary: This amazing privately owned 2-bedroom apartment will make you not want to leave. With the modern decor and comfortable clean lines in the living spaces, you’ll be able to relax, enjoy and entertain with views up La Trobe street and Elizabeth street. The location is absolutely perfect. You are opposite Melbourne Central with free transport to any part of the CBD.
space: Living Space The lounge has a great open concept with a simple Scandinavian design. You will fall in love with the floor to ceiling windows We really wanted you to have a comfortable space so we used various woods and light colours to create your lounge. The lounge has a 50” Smart HDTV with Netflix and a great Harmon Kardon sound system that can been seen and heard from the dinning room and kitchen.  Sleeping Space The bedroom feature a comfortable queen sized bed and ample storage for extended stays. Eating Space Open to the lounge is a dining room that can seat 4 people comfortably around the wood dining table. The kitchen has all of the essentials you need to whip up a meal and plenty of cupboard space for the extended stays. … Space There is one full bathroom in the front of the unit away from everything else.  Extra Space You will have the pleasure of having a private balcony in this beautiful apartment. There is also a washer/dryer combo located just beside the kitchen.
host_about:
LittleStay is a boutique short stay company specialising in homemade hospitality. We are passionate about traveling, exploring, and sharing. Bitten by the travel bug when we were young, we love to jump on a plane and explore the world. Spending our days and nights away from home with new friends, exchanging our experiences, and building new unforgettable memories. LittleStay is here to help create those memories. 

That's the idyllic part, but in our real life we all have bills, mortgages and obligations that we wish we could leave at home and don't have to travel with.

Consequentially LittleStay was born to help with that dream, a company that allow people like us and others to travel, live, experience or start a new life without the everyday struggle of life back “home”.

LittleStay wants you to feel comfortable entrusting us with your largest asset. We will consider your home our home while we manage it. It is our reputation on the line if something is amiss. We do not take that lightly.  LittleStay wants you to be a part of our LittleFamily. We value your partnership and thusly, if you are holidaying and want to stay at one of our properties, you’ll receive insider rates. You can even reserve your own property for your family and friends that are visiting. 

We take care of virtually everything. Our level of cleaning is second to none. Our customer service is beyond compare. Our commitment to you, the owner, our guest, our community is unquestionable. 

We believe a happy home is a filled home so if you have a property that is not happy, please contact us to see how we can help you. 

Or if you're one of our amazing guests helping us, please let us know how we can make your stay more enjoyable. 

Warmest Regards
The LittleStay Team

Meet Lou and Tanya.

We started doing Airbnb in February 2014 in Toronto and have loved all of the experiences it created for us. 

Now we have resettled from our global exploration in Melbourne, Australia.
We have a house and share with another couple Luke and Adam we are all excited to make our home available to other like minded travelers.

Tanya is a born and bred Torontonian, who manages the creative department for a marketing agency. Lou is an Australian born traveling gnome, who works as an event manager running sporting events.

We enjoy photography, creative design, sudoku competitions, building furniture, and cooking (in particular asian meals!)

We are often rarely home and often take impromptu weekend vacations, but also love meeting new people and could quite possibly be available to show you around Melbourne or definitely give you some helpful tips.

Eye-catching artworks prompt conversation and bring warmth and personality to the largely white palette, while black accents create a stylish contrast. The kitchen is a dreamy place to cook with its oversized island bench, chandeliers, butler’s pantry, mirror backsplash and sleek white cabinetry. After preparing a snack or meal, take a seat in the dining room where the atmosphere is refreshing and relaxing, while for a more sophisticated experience, open the floor-to-ceiling glass doors and get comfortable in the private formal dining room. The spacious living zone, with its velvet modular lounge, brings everyone together, or simply sit in peace as the kids head outdoors. There’s a seamless connection between indoor and outdoor living and you’re sure to gravitate to the modern grey and black scheme of the outdoor e

Why stay in a hotel when you can enjoy the space and amenity of a designer home?

Luxico manages designer and luxury homes across Melbourne, Sydney, Palm Beach, Byron Bay, Noosa and the Mornington Peninsula with many new locations coming in 2018.

All Luxico homes are  fully equipped with 5-star linens, towels, luxury toiletries, gourmet welcome hampers, free Wi-Fi and all the essential items that you will require during your stay.

Luxico's Housekeeping and Concierge Services teams are on hand to assist with airport transfers, grocery deliveries, catering, extra cleaning and anything else you might require.

Guests travelling with children can request toys, activities, travel cots and high chairs, whilst pet owners have a number of great properties to choose from with doggy beds, water bowls and other items provided to minimize your luggage.

Unrestricted street parking is available (with a permit)  MASTER BEDROOM - Luxury queen size bed - Bedside table - Wardrobes - Access to lightwell SECOND BEDROOM - 2 X Single beds - Bedside tables - Wardrobes - Dryer LIVING AREA - TV - Couches, chairs - Coffee table BATHROOM - Fresh towels  - Shampoo, conditioner, body wash, soap - Hair dryer - Toilet rolls KITCHEN - Complimentary coffee, tea, sugar, milk - Microwave - Refrigerator - Dishwasher - Stove, oven - Pots, pans, dishes, silverware, mugs, cups, cooking utensils - Tea towels LAUNDRY FACILITI
host_about:
G'day,

I'm Joel, i'm born and raised in Sydney, which is in my opinion one of the most beautiful major cities in the world. My goal in life is to one day visit every country in the world, I hold no bias to any of them and hope that I get the opportunity. So far I have visited 42 countries. Last year I spent 1 year travelling in South and Central America and loved the opportunity I had to learn Spanish. It was a great experience and one that I will never forget. 

My hobbies include all forms of board sports, skating, surfing and snowboarding primarily. I enjoy learning about new cultures especially their foods. I grew up in an Italian restaurant so my love for food and cooking is deeply engrained in my personality. 

My style of hosting and living life in general is pretty relaxed. I will do my best to greet you at the door and make your stay as enjoyable as possible. But if you just want to chill I can totally relate. 

I also love music and watching live music. I mostly go out to see House, deep house and techno music as that scene in Sydney is easily accessible. However at home you will find me listening to hip-hop, reggae, latin, afro-beat, jazz and anything with a smooth and funky beat. 

If you need recommendations about food or music in Sydney these are probably my two strongest topics, so please don't hesitate. 

Looking forward to meeting more crazy, fun and cool people through Airbnb. 

Joel

name: 1920s Brunswick: B'fast, Tram, Cats
summary: A beautiful 1920s brick house one minute's walk to cafes and trams going past Melbourne Zoo and Victoria Market, with Brunswick cafe culture a stroll away. Enjoy a spacious room with bay window and a sunny back garden.
space: Welcome to our generous single-storey (3 bedroom, 1.5 bathroom) house, art deco stylings circa 1920. Indulge in Brunswick's cafe culture, take the tram out your front door to Melbourne Zoo, Royal Park, or Victoria Market, or just languish with the magnificent weeping elm out the front. The room offers high ceilings, a ceiling fan for hotter days, and a sturdy fold-out sofabed, comfortable for two. Bedding is available for a third person with a small extra charge. We are on a convenient street, bordering nearby Melville Rd. Cafes, takeaways and a small supermarket are just around the corner, and two minutes' tram ride takes you to the Union Square shopping precinct.  Brunswick West is a Melbourne suburb 6km north of the CBD, and a lovely quiet spot in the greater Brunswick precinct. 15 minutes' walk or 3 on the bus gets you to hip shopping, cafes, and all sorts of odds and sods on Sydney Rd. 5 minutes' drive gets you onto the Citylink, with another twenty minutes to Melbourne Airport -
host_about: A self confessed classical music tragic, I live for music, art and cats! As a musician I have travelled Australia extensively and know the country well.  As a host, my house is yours to share and I will help you make the most of your time here. I am passionate about caring for the environment and have solar panels for energy needs and chooks to minimize any household food wastage. I love food but like to leave the car at home when possible so live near the tram that takes you to the amazing Victoria market.

Hi,

I love Melbourne, particularly when it's sunny and love being at home and tending to our fruit and veg - oh and hanging out in our backyard and in the gardens across the road.

I hope that you enjoy your stay in Melbourne and particularly if you stay at this house. 

Thanks,
Ellie

How to describe oneself?
Philosophy comes to mind first - karma is simple enough to strive to live by. 
I hosted in Fitzroy, Melbourne (Australia); I loved being immersed in the vibrant artist culture there (and all that goes along with it).
I find myself now, running a newly-opened vegan cafe (next door!) with my partner Hari. Working hard to get the place off the ground, in the 'off season' I'm sure I'll be back to my pastimes: reading, crypto, music, art, yoga, dancing. 
The highlight of my day? bonding with some beautiful travelers who have been frequenting our cafe. 
I hope to meet you :)
Namaste

host_about:
Hi, my name is Valeria. My husband Ben and I own and manage a number of upmarket guesthouses located in the inner Melbourne suburbs. 

We specialise in offering a new and unique opportunity to overseas, inter and intrastate visitors, career professionals, academics, post and undergraduates (3rd year and over), trainees, language students, doctors, teachers and other business specialists to gain superior inner Melbourne accommodation and lessen the stresses of moving to a new town, new state or a new country.

We offer fully furnished, centrally located properties with plenty of parking and quality fixtures and furnishings, each has an alfresco entertainment area and BBQ in a garden setting, a fully equipped property in an exclusive professional apartment house environment, where new arrivals, to Melbourne, or people going through a lifestyle transition, can experience an instant community atmosphere for medium (from two weeks), or long term stays, and say goodbye to lonely, restrictive and expensive apartment living.

No more solitary TV dinners! Each property provides apartment house accommodation on a room-by-room basis with shared kitchen, dining and lounge facilities. This style of apartment house living provides opportunities for new arrivals, to Melbourne to quickly, form friendships, build networks with other likeminded people and settle more easily into a new life. This helps to alleviate homesickness and improves their effectiveness in the workplace or place of learning.

A safe and comfortable home life makes for a happier Melbourne experience.

Typical Tenant Profiles

Flexi (Hidden by Airbnb) is open to a wide range of people from professional backgrounds usually between (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) years of age. Typical residents are overseas, inter and intrastate visitors, corporate and career professionals, academics, post and undergraduates (3rd year and over), trainees, language students, doctors, nurses, teachers and other specialists or people in the throes of re-establishing a home and life in Melbourne.

Ben and I hope you choose to stay with us and we have the opportunity to make your stay in Melbourne a life long happy memory.

Hi, my name is Valeria. My husband Ben and I own and manage a number of upmarket guesthouses located in the inner Melbourne suburbs. 

We specialise in offering a new and unique opportunity to overseas, inter and intrastate visitors, career professionals, academics, post and undergraduates (3rd year and over), trainees, language students, doctors, teachers and other business specialists to gain superior inner Melbourne accommodation and lessen the stresses of moving to a new town, new state or a new country.

We offer fully furnished, centrally located properties with plenty of parking and quality fixtures and furnishings, each has an alfresco entertainment area and BBQ in a garden setting, a fully equipped property in an exclusive professional apartment house environment, where new arrivals, to Melbourne, or people going through a lifestyle transition, can experience an instant community atmosphere for medium (from two weeks), or long term stays, and say goodbye to lonely, restrictive and expensive apartment living.

No more solitary TV dinners! Each property provides apartment house accommodation on a room-by-room basis with shared kitchen, dining and lounge facilities. This style of apartment house living provides opportunities for new arrivals, to Melbourne to quickly, form friendships, build networks with other likeminded people and settle more easily into a new life. This helps to alleviate homesickness and improves their effectiveness in the workplace or place of learning.

A safe and comfortable home life makes for a happier Melbourne experience.

Typical Tenant Profiles

Flexi (Hidden by Airbnb) is open to a wide range of people from professional backgrounds usually between (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) years of age. Typical residents are overseas, inter and intrastate visitors, corporate and career professionals, academics, post and undergraduates (3rd year and over), trainees, language students, doctors, nurses, teachers and other specialists or people in the throes of re-establishing a home and life in Melbourne.

Ben and I hope you choose to stay with us and we have the opportunity to make your stay in Melbourne a life long happy memory.

host_about:
Hi.  I am happy to say that I come from the melting pot of creation.  My genealogy is sourced from British, Scottish, Irish, French, Spanish, German and Indian blood.  As such I am a lover of all cultures. I was born in India and lived there for 15 years prior to migrating to Australia with parents, grandparents and 5 siblings.  I have two sisters and three brothers.

When it comes to food I love Indian curries having been nurtured by my late maternal grandmother who was of French and Indian stock.  These curries were particularly unique, developed over two centuries of what we call Anglo-Indian culture.  Yet I also enjoy the rich heritage of Anglo European cuisine which I have inherited from both sides of my family.
You get the picture - I love food and I like nothing more than cooking for other people.
I have travelled too - North America, Canada, England, Paris, Latvia, India, Thailand, Cambodia, Laos, Vietnam, China, Malaysia, Singapore and Indonesia. I have also briefly spent time in Vanuatu and Fiji and while the weather and activities were great they have not drawn me back. My home country of course tops the list especially as I still have a home there.  But Latvia in summer and Lake Toba in Sumatra have been the pearls of my journeys.

But it is hard to say I really like one thing/culture/place more than the other.  My home in Bindi is the place I go to when I want to wind down from my work in the Intellectual Disability sector.  At Bindi I find peace of mind and can settle down with my children to play scrabble, boggle and jigsaw puzzles.  At other times I can relax by doing some work on the property.  With three acres there is lots to do. On cooler days I go hiking into the forest or four wheel driving.  Occasionally I ride the dirt bike into the nearby hills.  At other times I drop a line in the river for a trout or go for a swim.  Though I must say my daughters have always caught the bigger fish.  Then there are great reads by Wilbur Smith and Bill Bryson just to name a couple.

I love live theatre, opera, musicals and comedy.  One of the more recent productions I enjoyed was Chinese Opera about the three kingdoms and I watched this in Chengdu, Sichuan, China in August 2016. Other musicals that I have loved are Phantom of the Opera and Les Miserables but the production of Lion King did not meet my expectations.  I like music from the 50's to the 80's as well as Classical.  So if you decide to visit Bindi for an AirBnB stay you will find quite a selection.  Just to name a few performers - BB King, U2, Dire Straits, Crowded House, Men at Work, Michael Buble, Brahms, Beethoven and so on.

Sadly, as much as I would like to be there all the time to host my guests my work with people with a disability is my passion.  It is not just a career, it is a vocation in which I plan to spend the rest of my life.

However, I do get to Bindi every 2nd weekend and it would be a pleasure to host and to show you the pleasures that the local area has to offer.

As such I am offering people the opportunity to enjoy what I have to share with or without my presence and to make themselves at home.  What I do ask is that you treat the opportunity to rest and recuperate in a pristine setting with as much respect as you give your own home and family.

Formerly I was an engineer and believed that life was very structured and controlled.  I did that for 19 years and one day felt I needed a change.  After another 22 years working with people with a disability I have grown in the knowledge that life cannot be controlled but can be enjoyed.

My catchcry now is "There is no such thing as a disability because we are all differently able". I know this well, having experienced a minor disability in 1985 losing three fingers in an industrial accident. I believe that "if you can dream it you can do it".

host_about:
G'day,

I'm Joel, i'm born and raised in Sydney, which is in my opinion one of the most beautiful major cities in the world. My goal in life is to one day visit every country in the world, I hold no bias to any of them and hope that I get the opportunity. So far I have visited 42 countries. Last year I spent 1 year travelling in South and Central America and loved the opportunity I had to learn Spanish. It was a great experience and one that I will never forget. 

My hobbies include all forms of board sports, skating, surfing and snowboarding primarily. I enjoy learning about new cultures especially their foods. I grew up in an Italian restaurant so my love for food and cooking is deeply engrained in my personality. 

My style of hosting and living life in general is pretty relaxed. I will do my best to greet you at the door and make your stay as enjoyable as possible. But if you just want to chill I can totally relate. 

I also love music and watching live music. I mostly go out to see House, deep house and techno music as that scene in Sydney is easily accessible. However at home you will find me listening to hip-hop, reggae, latin, afro-beat, jazz and anything with a smooth and funky beat. 

If you need recommendations about food or music in Sydney these are probably my two strongest topics, so please don't hesitate. 

Looking forward to meeting more crazy, fun and cool people through Airbnb. 

Joel

host_about:
Hi! I was born and bred in Melbourne and I love my home city. I am addicted to travelling and have been to over 20 countries now. Some of my favourites are India, UK and USA.

I finished my degree in business (entrepreneurship to be specific) in 2015 and love talking about different business ideas. I also have a passion for all types of art, especially street art - if you're interested in a tour I'm also an Airbnb Experience Host!! I've recently developed Australia's most popular long-distance ride sharing app called Buckle Up. If you want to find out more about it (and maybe booking some transport along the Great Ocean Road or to/from Sydney) please search for 'Buckle Up' in the App Store / G Play. 

I try to make my apartments as socially responsible as I can. For example, I supply organic, fair trade tea and coffee for my guests in addition to using Who Gives A Crap toilet paper (they donate 50% of profits to WaterAid which helps provide clean water and sanitation projects around the world). I know these small additions may not have a huge impact on the world but every little bit counts! 

If you book one of my apartments, I will give you all sorts of helpful hints as to where to see the best music, art, bars and other great things Melbourne has to offer. I hope you find what you're looking for in one of my properties and I meet you soon!

Motto: "Humankind; be both!"

Kangaroo Ridge Retreat offers a secluded and private cabin, with magnificent views in every room.  Your cabin is fitted with its own double spa bath, a balcony, and a kitchenette with everything you need. Relax and watch the changing colours of the mountains as the sun sets in the west, from your bed, the lounge, the kitchen or even the spa! All stays include seasonal breakfast provisions that can be enjoyed at your time and pace.  The concept of Kangaroo Ridge Retreat is that you have everything you need for retreating. Experience the taste of the area without even leaving your cabin. Choose optional extras for your breakfast, create a light meal or take a gourmet sandwich with you on a day trip. With local whites, reds and locally made beers and ciders, you need only journey six steps from your couch to toast out the day. It’s a Yarra Valley deli in your room!

Simon is originally from Germany and Rebecca is from Australia and we currently call Healesville our home. Simon works in the city, while Rebecca is a researcher at the University of Melbourne. summary: Unknown
space: I have a sofabed in my house in Yarraville.  Formerly a working-class suburb, in recent years Yarraville has experienced rapid gentrification due to its proximity to the Melbourne city centre. Yarraville lies immediately north of the West Gate Bridge, and immediately west of its namesake, the Yarra River. Anderson and Ballarat Streets, in the heart of the Yarraville Village, are lined with refurbished 19th century buildings and dotted with quaint neighbourhood cafés, restaurants and boutique shops. This village atmosphere is anchored by the restored Sun Theatre and the adjacent Sun bookshop. Notable examples of Edwardian and Victorian architecture can be found in Yarraville. The Yarraville Village is home to many award-winning restaurants and cafes. A reflection of Melbourne’s multicultural nature, Yarraville offers an array of world cuisine styles including Greek, Italian, Modern Asian, Indian, Cambodian, Thai, Chinese and Modern Australian.

Hello

I am very easy going, friendly, thoughtful and respectful.  I seek the same in guests. I want my guests to feel like they have found a home away from home, where they too can relax and make the most of their time away with privacy.

I like to share good food and wine, which extends to loving to cook for friends.  Cooking and entertaining in the common areas is a treat.  Why don’t you stay and check it out? :)

Mike and I have been together for decades and enjoy the opportunities we have for adventures on our tandem bike and fun with good friends and family.

host_about:
Hi, my name is Valeria. My husband Ben and I own and manage a number of upmarket guesthouses located in the inner Melbourne suburbs. 

We specialise in offering a new and unique opportunity to overseas, inter and intrastate visitors, career professionals, academics, post and undergraduates (3rd year and over), trainees, language students, doctors, teachers and other business specialists to gain superior inner Melbourne accommodation and lessen the stresses of moving to a new town, new state or a new country.

We offer fully furnished, centrally located properties with plenty of parking and quality fixtures and furnishings, each has an alfresco entertainment area and BBQ in a garden setting, a fully equipped property in an exclusive professional apartment house environment, where new arrivals, to Melbourne, or people going through a lifestyle transition, can experience an instant community atmosphere for medium (from two weeks), or long term stays, and say goodbye to lonely, restrictive and expensive apartment living.

No more solitary TV dinners! Each property provides apartment house accommodation on a room-by-room basis with shared kitchen, dining and lounge facilities. This style of apartment house living provides opportunities for new arrivals, to Melbourne to quickly, form friendships, build networks with other likeminded people and settle more easily into a new life. This helps to alleviate homesickness and improves their effectiveness in the workplace or place of learning.

A safe and comfortable home life makes for a happier Melbourne experience.

Typical Tenant Profiles

Flexi (Hidden by Airbnb) is open to a wide range of people from professional backgrounds usually between (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) years of age. Typical residents are overseas, inter and intrastate visitors, corporate and career professionals, academics, post and undergraduates (3rd year and over), trainees, language students, doctors, nurses, teachers and other specialists or people in the throes of re-establishing a home and life in Melbourne.

Ben and I hope you choose to stay with us and we have the opportunity to make your stay in Melbourne a life long happy memory.

Hosting people in our lovely old B&B home is what I do. With a lovely team of helpers, we run the award winning Captains Retreat B&B as well as numerous apartments and cottages here in beautiful, historic, waterside Williamstown.  

Interests: Art, Music, Sport, Travel, Movies, Good Food, Good Wine, Good Company and not last by any means Animals, in particular Cats. (note though that Simba and Leo (my so called Lions) are not allowed int the guest part of the house). 

Our lovely old home is just one door from the water, marina and restaurants and has been tastefully renovated so that every room has ensuites (some with spas) and half of the rooms also have gas log fires. One of the rooms has its own private lounge and balcony but other guests can enjoy their choice of two shared lounge rooms as well as a large north facing balcony and delightful private walled garden. 

Other than beds (which are new and very comfortable!!),  I love to buy antique and pre-loved furniture and  have them restored using classic and sometimes quirky fabrics. 

I'm proud to say that we have won numerous awards including 'tourism' and 'hospitality' at the Hobsons Bay region Business excellence awards (3 times) as well as taken out the People's Choice award for the state of Victoria twice in the last three awards. 

Most of our guests are business people or travellers so you can be assured of a quiet, relaxing and private 'home award from home' experience. 
We look forward to welcoming you Williamstown.

host_about:
I'm a passionate creative with way to many hobbies. I live with my partner Uscha and our new son Louis. I love the outdoors and enjoy mornings chasing waves, riding down mountains and soaking up the sun. Love a good home cooked breaky shared with family and friends then I'm ready to start the day. 

Uscha and run a business together so we're lucky to share most days side by side or swapping work duties for taking care of our little man often through out the day. 

I love to travel too and we often do travel for work and pleasure, able to mix both frequently. Life is pretty dam good and I'm grateful to have such a beautiful, kind and talented partner, an amazing little boy, a great job and an abundance activities to keep me busy.

Just seems to be not enough time in the day. Well there's always tomorrow!

Passions: Family, kung fu, surfing, dancing, mountain biking, playing music - guitar, congas, good food, specially home cooked with love, wine and friends.

Hi, my name is Valeria. My husband Ben and I own and manage a number of upmarket guesthouses located in the inner Melbourne suburbs. 

We specialise in offering a new and unique opportunity to overseas, inter and intrastate visitors, career professionals, academics, post and undergraduates (3rd year and over), trainees, language students, doctors, teachers and other business specialists to gain superior inner Melbourne accommodation and lessen the stresses of moving to a new town, new state or a new country.

We offer fully furnished, centrally located properties with plenty of parking and quality fixtures and furnishings, each has an alfresco entertainment area and BBQ in a garden setting, a fully equipped property in an exclusive professional apartment house environment, where new arrivals, to Melbourne, or people going through a lifestyle transition, can experience an instant community atmosphere for medium (from two weeks), or long term stays, and say goodbye to lonely, restrictive and expensive apartment living.

No more solitary TV dinners! Each property provides apartment house accommodation on a room-by-room basis with shared kitchen, dining and lounge facilities. This style of apartment house living provides opportunities for new arrivals, to Melbourne to quickly, form friendships, build networks with other likeminded people and settle more easily into a new life. This helps to alleviate homesickness and improves their effectiveness in the workplace or place of learning.

A safe and comfortable home life makes for a happier Melbourne experience.

Typical Tenant Profiles

Flexi (Hidden by Airbnb) is open to a wide range of people from professional backgrounds usually between (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) years of age. Typical residents are overseas, inter and intrastate visitors, corporate and career professionals, academics, post and undergraduates (3rd year and over), trainees, language students, doctors, nurses, teachers and other specialists or people in the throes of re-establishing a home and life in Melbourne.

Ben and I hope you choose to stay with us and we have the opportunity to make your stay in Melbourne a life long happy memory.

We enjoy galleries, museums, historic areas and walking in the natural outdoors. We prefer self catering to hotels. We are both ex Secondary School teachers. Jan has been Coordinator of Education at the Immigration museum in Melbourne for the last 10 years. Rick has been a self employed builder for 29 years. We are very reliable and always leave a rental apartment in exactly the same condition as we find it.
As experienced users of Airbnb we understand that prompt and effective communication between host and visitor is very important. We have had many wonderful stays and will now return the hospitality to our guests.

host_about:
Hi my name is Dawei, I started doing Airbnb September 2015. 

I'm a 20 years old undergraduate student currently studying commercial law. I like to watch movies and play video games. Sometimes I could spend my whole day in my room just play games. I thought that there isn't much things to do outside and I thought the World was a boring place. When I'm not playing games, I would read news on the internet just to catch up with the rest of the world. That's how I knew Airbnb. 

One day, my father come to me, talked about doing short term renting. He has got few new apartments that our relatives bought which needs to be rented out. I told him about Airbnb and he thought we could really make it work. So I asked my best friend if he is interested to be my partner for this, and he said yes. We started almost immediately, planning, buying furnitures to started taking guests in just two weeks. 

Then it really changed me.

I met with travellers around the world. Every body was so polite and friendly.  When I talk to them I can feel the excitement and happiness. It's totally  different compare to what I thought people are like. Maybe because this communicate is great, I don't know.  Then I  thought "I want to be people like my guests". I want people around me to feel life is great and there are a lot to look forward to. The guests really gave me a lot motivation towards my work and my life. Here I have to thank you all.

After one month, the revenue was great, however take away the interests and loans, all kinds of fees and salary for my partner, there are really not much left for me. But I think that's enough, I'm still a student, I have to spend time on study and don't have much things to spend money on anyway, being able to save money for a holiday with my girl friend every few month is perfect for me. 

After all these experience, I felt it really changed my life and how I view the world. Doesn't matter if I fail or succeed it's  going to effect the rest of my life in a very positive way, that's something really valuable to me.

name: LUSATIA COTTAGE Accommodation
summary: This beautiful country cottage is set on a working Dexter cattle farm. The perfect retreat for any couple wanting to escape the hustle and bustle of city life.  Keep to yourself and enjoy the serenity, or make an appointment and experience farm life.
space: This is a working farm, so don't be surprised to hear a tractor or see the farmer working in the paddocks.     We are happy if you want to keep to yourself, but also more than happy to show you around the property and introduce you to our beautiful Dexter cattle.  The Cottage is set in a mainly private setting, overlooking a small paddock.  It is small but comfortable, with all you will need to enjoy a country get-a-way. There is one bedroom with a lovely queen size bed and the couch pulls out to a double sofa bed, so the Cottage can comfortably sleep 4.  (The bathroom is off the bedroom, so 2 couples sharing will need to negotiate this).   It is a great space for a small family with a porta cot available.  The kitchen is well equipped and you could easily cook up a meal with the microwave, electric fry pan/skillet or the BBQ.  All your linen and towels are supplied, and there will be some breakfast supplies for your first morning.
host_about: I am in a great place in my life right now.  New partner and a fabulous new business venture.  Life is good.   I am enjoying being able to share the beautiful Yarra Valley with so many guests.  Having my place in Healesville has been such a joy, and now our new place in Woori Yallock is ready to go.  Apart from my business I live and work on a beautiful property in Woori Yallock where my partner and I run Dexter cattle.   We  breed cattle, tend to our vegie patch, collect eggs from the chickens and enjoy a quite drink after a hard days work.  Farm life is so fulfilling.

host_about:
We're Klaudia (Sanctuary Artist), Jonathan (Data Magician), Maria (Fairy Godmother) and Tony (Maker of Worlds), a multi-cultural family all living in Melbourne. We're all different in many ways, but we all share one thing in common: passion for unique and magical experiences. 

We have long since wished there were easy ways to escape our busy city lives and retreat into a magical, beautiful and peaceful space that feels like another world. This idea eventually evolved into a mission to build with our own hands Melbourne's very own magical sanctuaries, and to share it with the rest of the world.

We love imagining what we could create, to build, and to share them with the world through hosting. We constantly think about how to make our creations bring  even greater sense of joy and wonder, and not about how much it'll cost us. We're genuinely excited and happy to host each new guest, to hear about what they love about our creations, and what we could do to make it even better.

We have built and opened our first instalment of Melbourne's hidden sanctuary, which we lovingly refer to as "Heaven & Earth". We have plans to make it even better, as well as other ideas for other worlds we want to try building for our next instalments.

We invite you to step into one of our hidden sanctuaries, to follow our journey on social media, and to watch and help us grow by sharing what you think!

host_about:
Hi, we’re Frank and Vince.

Thanks for reading our profile.

We love hosting, and when time permits, travelling!

As guests, we understand and appreciate the guest/host relationship, so will always be respectful of both you and your home, and look forward to sharing the experience.

As hosts, we thank you for considering us for your Melbourne stay. You can view all our airbnb apartments and homes here: https://www.airbnb.com.au/users/50121/listings

We've been welcoming guests to our homes since 2009, when we established 'a2c urban stays Melbourne', a collection of unique, hand-selected inner Melbourne properties, specifically designed for welcoming, memorable short stays.

Featuring stylish contemporary interiors, in the best lifestyle locations, our properties are situated in the very heart of Melbourne’s hippest inner-city areas. All our apartments and homes are within a short stroll of cafes, restaurants, shopping, night life and public transport. Cultural and sporting facilities including MCG/Hisense/Etihad Stadiums, Melbourne waterfront, Melbourne City Centre and some of Melbourne’s best beaches are easily accessible.

Our guests enjoy free wifi, superior comfort beds, high quality bed linens and towels, entertainment systems offering large flat screen TVs, sound systems, books, magazines, air-conditioning*, heating, full size fully equipped kitchens with Euro appliances, laundry facilities*, parking*, complimentary starter provisions and housekeeping service for longer stays*.
*Please enquire before booking.

Exceeding guest expectations is what we’re about.

If you’re looking for a truly special and authentic Melbourne experience, in a warm, stylish inviting space that is close to the many wonderful attractions our city is famous for, then we’re the perfect choice. Feel free to contact us and we’ll be happy to assist you plan your perfect stay.

As hosts, we look forward to welcoming you. As guests, we look forward to discovering your home and surrounds.

Warm regards,

Frank and Vince

host_about:
A mining engineer by profession, I have owned two other service businesses since 1998. I started StayCentral when I purchased one apartment in 2005, and now manage multiple properties in many different locations in inner Melbourne.

Like many of my guests, I love to travel; both overseas on epic journeys (including remote locations like the Mulu Caves in Borneo, ancient cities (in Nepal, Turkey, Peru & Jordan), Antarctica & Alaska, Torres del Paine and colourful markets in amazing places like Fa Long in Vietnam, Jaisalmer in India, & La Paz in Bolivia). I also love short domestic trips for weekends away just to relax. It means I get to be on the other side of the counter, and experience how other people look after their guests: and I take their good ideas back with me. 

(My manager, Max, has also travelled from afar to be here btw, and he can also speak with our guests in Russian and Ukranian).

I even worked as a part-time tourist guide in Melbourne for a couple of years, and really enjoyed the interactions with the tourists off the huge cruise liners that appear in Melbourne each spring and summer. I have tried to extend this experience into my accommodation business here at home, where I really love assisting people with their stays. You only need to read the 550 or so reviews on Airbnb, Trip advisor, Goo gle, and on my own StayCentral website to realise how much our guests enjoy our apartments, and the way we look after them. 

I like keeping fit with gym work and roller-blading; often blading 30 kms or so on a day out. I cook for my mates once a month, and have done so since 2007. I cook and they bring the wine; my other love since coming to Melbourne in 2003.

I love living in Melbourne. It enjoys a unique place in Australia. It is often described as the cultural, business, shopping and sporting capital of the country. The restaurants and cafes in Melbourne are amongst the best in the world. I love living in an urban village amongst these, and all the other everyday shops; and jumping on a tram and avoiding the hassles of traffic. It is a city of great opportunity, experiences, events and lifestyle that can be enjoyed by locals and visitors alike; and I really enjoy facilitating our guests' stays here.

StayCentral Melbourne Corporate Apartments is a unique group of serviced apartments in central Melbourne. We offer boutique short and long-stay accommodation for relocations, family holidays and getaways. Our comfortable apartments have also been enjoyed by employees and contractors, executives and people needing temporary accommodation. We even have many pet-friendly apartments available! We provide excellent customer service from the time you first contact us to make a booking, through to the end of your stay.

All of our properties from one-bedroom apartments to seven-bedroom mansions are close to all the everyday things our guests would need during their stay; from cafes, restaurants and supermarkets, to shops, trams and nightlife - yet all locations are generally very quiet.

All of our interiors have been designed by experienced interior designers, and you will experience that feeling of "I'm home!" when you walk in, make yourself a cuppa and put your feet up. We supply far more than tea and coffee etc. There are many extras that make your stay more pleasant for our guests; including shopping trolleys, free Netflix in most properties, umbrellas and book exchanges.

I do hope I have the opportunity to help you get to know Melbourne and grow to love it as I have.

host_about:
Hello,

My name is Anne. I am a 36 year old entrepreneur living in Melbourne  with my husband and kids.  I enjoy reading and learning about anything related to business and design as well as travelling and discovering new places.  

We are offering a private two bedroom apartment, nestled in the heart of Seddon Village.  It is a quiet but super friendly, suburb about 7km from Melbourne CBD.  The apartment sits on top of Seddon's main shopping strip which offers a variety of shops and cafes for your convenience as well as a train station within walking distance.  The apartment has been thoughtfully styled for your comfort and reflects the Scandinavian minimalist style which we have grown to love.  

As a traveller myself, I want to offer our guests a memorable experience by providing a clean and great space to relax and stay.  We help take the stress out of arriving in Melbourne for first time travellers by providing clear directions, self check-in instructions and  open communication at all times,  sharing local insights to Melbourne and what it has to offer. Booking this little Seddon Apartment will ensure you get to experience some of the very simple design elements we love having in our lives including indoor plants and art.

host_about:
Hi, my name is Valeria. My husband Ben and I own and manage a number of upmarket guesthouses located in the inner Melbourne suburbs. 

We specialise in offering a new and unique opportunity to overseas, inter and intrastate visitors, career professionals, academics, post and undergraduates (3rd year and over), trainees, language students, doctors, teachers and other business specialists to gain superior inner Melbourne accommodation and lessen the stresses of moving to a new town, new state or a new country.

We offer fully furnished, centrally located properties with plenty of parking and quality fixtures and furnishings, each has an alfresco entertainment area and BBQ in a garden setting, a fully equipped property in an exclusive professional apartment house environment, where new arrivals, to Melbourne, or people going through a lifestyle transition, can experience an instant community atmosphere for medium (from two weeks), or long term stays, and say goodbye to lonely, restrictive and expensive apartment living.

No more solitary TV dinners! Each property provides apartment house accommodation on a room-by-room basis with shared kitchen, dining and lounge facilities. This style of apartment house living provides opportunities for new arrivals, to Melbourne to quickly, form friendships, build networks with other likeminded people and settle more easily into a new life. This helps to alleviate homesickness and improves their effectiveness in the workplace or place of learning.

A safe and comfortable home life makes for a happier Melbourne experience.

Typical Tenant Profiles

Flexi (Hidden by Airbnb) is open to a wide range of people from professional backgrounds usually between (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) years of age. Typical residents are overseas, inter and intrastate visitors, corporate and career professionals, academics, post and undergraduates (3rd year and over), trainees, language students, doctors, nurses, teachers and other specialists or people in the throes of re-establishing a home and life in Melbourne.

Ben and I hope you choose to stay with us and we have the opportunity to make your stay in Melbourne a life long happy memory.

space: This apartment overlooks beautiful gardens and has everything you need for a comfortable stay including: -  2 good sized bedrooms in which the beds can be made up as either a king bed or split into two king single beds - a third bedroom with a queen bed and access to the outdoor patio - hotel quality linen and towels - a front balcony overlooking the gardens, tennis court and pool - a rear terrace with outdoor lounge furniture overlook trees and a quiet back street - a fully equiupped kitchen, including dishwasher and microwave, plates and cooking utensils - large bathroom with combined bath and shower - a separate toilet - a European laundry with washing machine and dryer - large flat screen television with cable television (Foxtel Platinum)
host_about:
Hi from Bronnie and Neil ;-)
We love being airbnb hosts and sharing our homes and our beautiful city with others.
We have been airbnb hosts for over four years and during that time we have met amazing and wonderful people from all around Australia and all parts of the world.
We started with the spare room in our own home and now have 20 properties, from high end luxury to family friendly apartments that we offer our guests. We even have a 7 bedroom, 7 bathroom mansion near the sea in St Kilda for larger groups! 
We use airbnb ourselves whenever we travel and feel we know what people are looking for. Good value, great locations, clean, comfortable and friendly! All our properties are in great locations, are professionally cleaned and we use hotel quality, commercially laundered linen on comfortable beds.  We meet all our guests on arrival to say hello and are on hand to offer help, advice and inside tips of places to go and things to see. 
Most of our properties include free parking which is a real bonus in the city and Foxtel (cable) television and other homely touches so you 'can live like a local'. (You can view our properties by clicking the View Full Profile link below and clicking on the listings on the left hand side of the page). 

A little bit about ourselves ... we're pretty easy going, and love getting out and about exploring different places. We are both keen travellers and have done our fair share of it in Australia and overseas - whether backpacking, camping, or an occasional splurge on 5-star resorts! You wouldn't call us 'party animals', but we do like socialising and meeting people.  We enjoy a wide variety of interests, love the movies, eating out, popping down to the beach on our scooter or pushbikes, and enjoying the many exciting sporting events and festivals that Melbourne has to offer.
Our motto is "strangers are just friends you haven't met yet!"
Wishing you happy travels and looking forward to meeting you soon :-)

Best regards
Bronnie and Neil

host_about:
I live in Elwood, Melbourne Australia. I am a Counsellor and have my own wellbeing business. 

I love travelling- and I really enjoy finding my own way around a new place. Often by walking around a new city, I discover the best hidden places- off the main tourist track. My favourite places, so far are: Southern France (Aix en Provence/Avignon/Montpellier/Antibes).. Italy, Spain and Asia. My apartment is a top floor private two bedroom oasis, that has everything one could desire. Set in a small block with only two other apartments in the building, it is top floor with view of rooftops (very parisian) & treetops.  With a cute little balcony, it is perfect for relaxing with a chilled drink after a relaxing day beachside. An under cover car space, within close proximity to the main entrance into the block. Wifi internet, laundry with washing machine & dryer, comfortable living area and fabulous, all amneties kitchen- it really is ideal. A stone's throw from stunning Elwood beach and a two min walk to the gorgeous Elwood village. 

I would welcome you to stay in my abode, and am quite sure you will have a wonderful experience of Melbourne, whilst having the comforts of this apartment to come home to at the end of a day.

host_about:
Professor Andrew MacLeod is a recognised global leader, negotiator and communicator. He has a track record of leading organisations through challenge, crisis and change and delivering policy advice to the highest level of government, business and academia.  
MacLeod’s negations successes include time as Chief of Operations of the UN Emergency Coordination Centre in Pakistan, where MacLeod negotiated a complex series of relationships that saw the Pakistan military, international NGOs, UN agencies, US military, UK military and non state militant groups all playing a role in delivering a successful operation without casualties or conflict. The innovative model of ‘Non Interfering Coordination’ has been documented in both The Pulse of Humanitarian Action (Fordham Press) and The Liaison Volume IV Issue 1, Centre for Excellence in Disaster Management.
At Cornerstone Capital MacLeod is a founding Non-Executive Director overseeing growth from start-up to ten figure (in US dollars) funds under advice and management in only 2 ½ years. While CEO of Committee for Melbourne, Professor MacLeod reversed three years of growing deficit to restore the organisation to financial sustainability. While Interim CEO of Good Super he re-established positive, working relationships with corporate regulators after the institution suffered ‘regulatory challenges’.

summary: Be welcomed into a beautiful Frida Kahlo style garden at the rear of our home in the most popular bayside area Elwood. space: Studio Moroc : a delightful open-plan peaceful space that allows you to truly unwind and relax.  Unique and filled with character this self contained apartment offers the perfect hideaway. The wooden slat panel ceiling provides calming texture and warmth - plus the bluestone bathroom with antique bifold door's and skylight is a lovely space for your cleansing routine. The kitchenette has a neat new double gas stove, microwave & small fridge. Studio Moroc is a perfect environment for those travelling on business or to make time for some yoga if that suits you - kick back with a wine, tea and a book. New Yorker magazines are provided to browse where you can always find something of interest. Studio Moroc is a private intimate retreat at the rear of a beautiful garden in a family home. It also has it's own little courtyard at the base of the apartment.  This private space is located in the most sought after golden mile of Elwood, beachside Melbourne.
host_about:
Elwood has a very friendly vibe & offers loads of variety -With it's beautiful leafy green streets and it's close proximity to everything it would have to be one of the finest & most relaxing areas to spend time in.
I've lived here in Elwood for 20 years and am married with a family, plus a small amusing looking dog called Luna. (a red Cavoodle).
We are perfectly positioned with only minutes from Elwood- St.Kilda beach & foreshore. Less than 10 mins walk to the light rail route 97 or a few mins walk to the public bus route 246. I mostly walk or bike ride everywhere, it's the best way to get around. 
We are surrounded by an abundance of restaurants & Bars - excellent beach front/foreshore , a great music scene, Arts culture, Theatre  cinemas, local farmers markets, Botanical gardens, The peanut farm in St.Kilda, Luna Park, a great local village shopping area _ whether it be Acland St, Carlisle st, Ormond Village or Supermarkets.
I enjoy making spaces look & feel beautiful so ambience is important to me.
Studio Moroc is a very private and quiet self contained apartment located at the rear of our garden & family home. 
Among other things I am self-employed and enjoy our busy life.
As a guest I'm extremely considerate, respectful and tidy.
As a host I welcome those that are similar. I am warm, friendly, clean ,a good communicator and very hospitable.

Studio Moroc is a perfect hideaway oasis and a lovely safe haven to return to after a long day out.

name: Art-Inspired Garden View Apartment
summary: Explore our artistically curated collection of canvas paintings in this central city apartment with stunning view of Flagstaff Gardens. With its unbeatable location with trams and train stations right at your doorstep, this is the perfect base from which to explore all Melbourne has to offer !
space: At Canvas Suites, we provide professionally laundered bath towels, hand towels, bed linens and premium L'Occitane bathroom amenities. The chiropedic Queen bed is complete with four luxurious mini pocket-spring pillows and high-warmth quilt, providing you with maximum support and comfort. The kitchen is fully equipped with pots and pans, utensils, crockery, salt, pepper and oil is at disposal if you want to prepare a home-cooked meal. There is also a capsule-style hot beverage machine set up in the kitchen, where a selection of capsules, both caffeinated and non-caffeinated are provided for your enjoyment. An assortment of teas is provided as well if that is what you prefer. Because Melbourne is such a fantastic city and to assist you in making the most out of your trip to Melbourne, we have carefully selected a number of coffee table books about Melbourne art, food and history and left them in the apartment for your reference and interest. A washer and dryer machine along with an iron
host_about:
Inspired by and dedicated to Australian contemporary artists, Canvas Suites aims to provide boutique hospitality experience to our guests. Each of our Suites are personally handpicked and meticulously setup as the place our guests call home when in Melbourne.

At Canvas Suites, we believe that no visit to a place is complete without immersing oneself in its unique culture and central to any culture is its art. We view each of our art-inspired Suites as carefully curated galleries with walls adorned by original Australian works of art which our guests may enjoy in private during their stay.

But great spaces with great art do not by themselves create great hospitality experience. We know what counts for our guests to have a great stay in Melbourne – a friendly face to meet them, top-of-the-line chiropedic beds made with pristine sheets, the towels and toiletries taken care of to our exacting standards. We also know that our guests want the space and freedom to experience what Melbourne has to offer at their own pace. So we are available 24/7 for when our guests need us, but we step back when they do not.

space: The dining table folds out to seat everyone or when not in use can be packed away to maximize the use of the space. The bedroom has a new twin bed that can be setup as 2 Single Beds or 1 King Sized Bed (let us know what you prefer in advance so we can prepare it for you). The bathroom has laundry facilities with a washing machine and dryer so you can do your washing if you're staying for a little while or stopping over during a long trip in Australia.  The kitchen is fully kitted out with everything you need including pots and pans, all the cutlery and crockery to have a meal at home if you want (but why would you when so many amazing cafes and restaurants are here in Melbourne!). Wifi internet is included of course too so you can get a bit of work done or have a night in front of the TV streaming online content if you're feeling a bit worn out after soaking up this great city. The TV has apps like Netflix but you will need your own subscription to use them.
host_about:
I'm Linton, I own and run a short-stay management company, Beyond a Room, here in Melbourne. If you book with me you'll be communicating with both myself and my staff.

I’m an entrepreneur, architecture graduate, photographer, cyclist (NOT the lycra kind), volunteer, adventurer and problem solver.

During my studies I worked at various cafes and architecture offices to save up for shoestring trips around the world. My grandma once told me I had ‘champagne taste but a beer budget’ and it’s a motto I’ve enjoyed applying to different parts of my life to get the more out of less and find enjoyment in the little things.

I love discovering authentic experiences when I travel and I love being able to share the opportunity with others, to live like a local when they travel too.

Some of my most memorable trips have been couch-surfin across Russia while taking the Trans Siberian, living in Helsinki and learning to hand build furniture, riding a vintage steel bicycle through France to race in L’Eroica and buying a car on craigzlist in Los Angeles and driving across the south, east and north coasts to arrive in Vancouver.

My listings are all managed by Beyond a Room and are all given names that I think reflect the character of the property and area. My aim is to give guests a unique and local perspective on the location and share my knowledge and experience of this wonderful city with travellers so that they feel at home. Search Beyond a Room to find out more about how we can help manage your airbnb.

I try to keep all my calendars up to date so if it’s available in the calendar, you can usually just go ahead and book

host_about:
A mining engineer by profession, I have owned two other service businesses since 1998. I started StayCentral when I purchased one apartment in 2005, and now manage multiple properties in many different locations in inner Melbourne.

Like many of my guests, I love to travel; both overseas on epic journeys (including remote locations like the Mulu Caves in Borneo, ancient cities (in Nepal, Turkey, Peru & Jordan), Antarctica & Alaska, Torres del Paine and colourful markets in amazing places like Fa Long in Vietnam, Jaisalmer in India, & La Paz in Bolivia). I also love short domestic trips for weekends away just to relax. It means I get to be on the other side of the counter, and experience how other people look after their guests: and I take their good ideas back with me. 

(My manager, Max, has also travelled from afar to be here btw, and he can also speak with our guests in Russian and Ukranian).

I even worked as a part-time tourist guide in Melbourne for a couple of years, and really enjoyed the interactions with the tourists off the huge cruise liners that appear in Melbourne each spring and summer. I have tried to extend this experience into my accommodation business here at home, where I really love assisting people with their stays. You only need to read the 550 or so reviews on Airbnb, Trip advisor, Goo gle, and on my own StayCentral website to realise how much our guests enjoy our apartments, and the way we look after them. 

I like keeping fit with gym work and roller-blading; often blading 30 kms or so on a day out. I cook for my mates once a month, and have done so since 2007. I cook and they bring the wine; my other love since coming to Melbourne in 2003.

I love living in Melbourne. It enjoys a unique place in Australia. It is often described as the cultural, business, shopping and sporting capital of the country. The restaurants and cafes in Melbourne are amongst the best in the world. I love living in an urban village amongst these, and all the other everyday shops; and jumping on a tram and avoiding the hassles of traffic. It is a city of great opportunity, experiences, events and lifestyle that can be enjoyed by locals and visitors alike; and I really enjoy facilitating our guests' stays here.

StayCentral Melbourne Corporate Apartments is a unique group of serviced apartments in central Melbourne. We offer boutique short and long-stay accommodation for relocations, family holidays and getaways. Our comfortable apartments have also been enjoyed by employees and contractors, executives and people needing temporary accommodation. We even have many pet-friendly apartments available! We provide excellent customer service from the time you first contact us to make a booking, through to the end of your stay.

All of our properties from one-bedroom apartments to seven-bedroom mansions are close to all the everyday things our guests would need during their stay; from cafes, restaurants and supermarkets, to shops, trams and nightlife - yet all locations are generally very quiet.

All of our interiors have been designed by experienced interior designers, and you will experience that feeling of "I'm home!" when you walk in, make yourself a cuppa and put your feet up. We supply far more than tea and coffee etc. There are many extras that make your stay more pleasant for our guests; including shopping trolleys, free Netflix in most properties, umbrellas and book exchanges.

I do hope I have the opportunity to help you get to know Melbourne and grow to love it as I have.

Hi, I am a painter and mosaic artist and love to create an environment for my guests that is relaxing and inspiring. My home is architecturally designed with open and airy rooms with art and mosaics spilling from the house and into the garden!
I run adult mosaic workshops and children's art classes from my studio.
I love travelling and have travelled to many places around the world. 
One of my greatest travelling achievements was walking 800km alone, on a pilgrimage across Spain. 
My next venture that I am planning to do is the Annapurna circuit in Nepal.
I love coffee shops, discovering new and interesting places and studying courses.  I always want to be learning new things and growing as a person. I am philosophical and spiritual and believe that life is our greatest teacher, bringing to us the experiences and people to challenge and enrich our lives. 
I look forward to sharing with you my home, my art and my heart! ( and my animals)

host_about:
Inspired by and dedicated to Australian contemporary artists, Canvas Suites aims to provide boutique hospitality experience to our guests. Each of our Suites are personally handpicked and meticulously setup as the place our guests call home when in Melbourne.

At Canvas Suites, we believe that no visit to a place is complete without immersing oneself in its unique culture and central to any culture is its art. We view each of our art-inspired Suites as carefully curated galleries with walls adorned by original Australian works of art which our guests may enjoy in private during their stay.

But great spaces with great art do not by themselves create great hospitality experience. We know what counts for our guests to have a great stay in Melbourne – a friendly face to meet them, top-of-the-line chiropedic beds made with pristine sheets, the towels and toiletries taken care of to our exacting standards. We also know that our guests want the space and freedom to experience what Melbourne has to offer at their own pace. So we are available 24/7 for when our guests need us, but we step back when they do not.

host_about:
G'day,

I'm Joel, i'm born and raised in Sydney, which is in my opinion one of the most beautiful major cities in the world. My goal in life is to one day visit every country in the world, I hold no bias to any of them and hope that I get the opportunity. So far I have visited 42 countries. Last year I spent 1 year travelling in South and Central America and loved the opportunity I had to learn Spanish. It was a great experience and one that I will never forget. 

My hobbies include all forms of board sports, skating, surfing and snowboarding primarily. I enjoy learning about new cultures especially their foods. I grew up in an Italian restaurant so my love for food and cooking is deeply engrained in my personality. 

My style of hosting and living life in general is pretty relaxed. I will do my best to greet you at the door and make your stay as enjoyable as possible. But if you just want to chill I can totally relate. 

I also love music and watching live music. I mostly go out to see House, deep house and techno music as that scene in Sydney is easily accessible. However at home you will find me listening to hip-hop, reggae, latin, afro-beat, jazz and anything with a smooth and funky beat. 

If you need recommendations about food or music in Sydney these are probably my two strongest topics, so please don't hesitate. 

Looking forward to meeting more crazy, fun and cool people through Airbnb. 

Joel

We also have a blow up mattress available to set up in the lounge for extra guests at no extra charge. The bathroom and kitchen have been newly renovated. There is a lovely courtyard to enjoy your meals and we have recently redone all the windows to draft proof and keep out the city noises.  We love to travel and believe that the most important thing in a hotel room is the comfort of the bed; If it is not to your liking we will do everything within reason to accommodate you.  Brand new super-warm gas fire recently installed to keep you toasty through winter :)
host_about: Early in 2014 I left a 12 year career in Information Technology to start a small chain of Launderettes with my partner in crime, Ben.  Our first is Soap Bar Carlton, a cosy and entertaining place to do your laundry, a hub of activity and a cafe to boot, with free wifi and mood lighting. Situated right next to our airbnb flat, a great place to grab your first coffee of the day.  We decided to airbnb our flat as we find the flat gets more love and respect with our wonderful guests then with full time tenants, so we furnished it with pre-loved furniture and brand new, top of the range, kitchenware and bedding, and enjoy meeting or at least hosting a range of lovely people.

host_about:
I'm Linton, I own and run a short-stay management company, Beyond a Room, here in Melbourne. If you book with me you'll be communicating with both myself and my staff.

I’m an entrepreneur, architecture graduate, photographer, cyclist (NOT the lycra kind), volunteer, adventurer and problem solver.

During my studies I worked at various cafes and architecture offices to save up for shoestring trips around the world. My grandma once told me I had ‘champagne taste but a beer budget’ and it’s a motto I’ve enjoyed applying to different parts of my life to get the more out of less and find enjoyment in the little things.

I love discovering authentic experiences when I travel and I love being able to share the opportunity with others, to live like a local when they travel too.

Some of my most memorable trips have been couch-surfin across Russia while taking the Trans Siberian, living in Helsinki and learning to hand build furniture, riding a vintage steel bicycle through France to race in L’Eroica and buying a car on craigzlist in Los Angeles and driving across the south, east and north coasts to arrive in Vancouver.

My listings are all managed by Beyond a Room and are all given names that I think reflect the character of the property and area. My aim is to give guests a unique and local perspective on the location and share my knowledge and experience of this wonderful city with travellers so that they feel at home. Search Beyond a Room to find out more about how we can help manage your airbnb.

I try to keep all my calendars up to date so if it’s available in the calendar, you can usually just go ahead and book

host_about:
Hi I’m Jack,

My wife Stacey and I have some amazing places in Melbourne and the Yarra Valley that we'd love to share with you. 

We have a stunning (circa 1854) converted stables in St Kilda, which is very close to Fitzroy and Acland Streets, the beach and many awesome cafes and restaurants and the Albert Park Formula One circuit. We have two stunning Art Deco apartments in the Botanic Garden’s precinct in Melbourne, which are close to the best of everything that Melbourne is famous for – shopping with Chapel St (South Yarra), Toorak Rd (South Yarra) & Bridge Rd (Richmond) all within walking distance to the best sports grounds in Australia including the MCG, Australian Open Tennis Arena, Melbourne Formula 1 Grand Prix and CBD all within 2 klms. South Yarra and the CBD have many of the best bars and restaurants and in typical Melbourne style you’ll have to scour the backstreets and laneways to find them.

Healesville Country House is our beautiful 5 bedroom home in the Yarra Valley, it is a former guesthouse circa 1900 that we've lovingly restored and created a family home from. We are two minutes from the main street and 5-10 minutes from some of the world's best wineries. It is the perfect place for unwinding with plenty of outdoor spaces including a pool and verandahs boasting some of the best views around.

Check out our profile for additional information and pictures. We're really happy to recommend our favourite restaurants, cafes and places to see. 
  
About us - I’m work with the best and brightest Australian technology and digital start-ups to help them become successful through investment and mentoring. Stacey is in the Fashion Industry and travels the world promoting emerging Australian brands to the rest of the world. We love everything about Melbourne, meeting new people, and travelling as much as we can – we are now eager to use AirBNB for all of our trips and hope to meet some of you through the process.

Hello - my name is Anthony and I live in Brunswick, Melbourne.

I am a musician and engineer and interested in finding solutions to climate change.

In my music work, I love singing, playing bass and performing. I do everything from performing at weddings, to parties, to busking (which I love).

I enjoy traveling  and exploring cities of the world, whether in Australia or overseas (Europe especially beguiling - London, Paris, Berlin). 

I am into sustainability, pretty relaxed and easygoing, don't smoke, and enjoy meeting up with friends for coffee and films  :)

Also, I have many interests, and tend to go out a lot of the time, rather than being house-bound.

AirBnB says to include a Life Motto ..... well, I like this one..... "Find something you love doing and you'll never work a day in your life"

Best Regards
Anthony

A bit about me.... I'm 41 years old, married with 2 sons. I purchased this apartment in 2005 and still use it as an office whenever vacant.
 
It would be my pleasure to welcome you to stay in this apartment whenever you are in Melbourne. Whether it is for a weekend or an extended stay for business or pleasure, I guarantee you will love living in this apartment.
 
Located in a secure complex in the heart of Port Melbourne, with common amenities such as a gym, two large swimming pools and a spa. There is a choice of three beautiful parks on the doorstep and the beach and local shopping strip with bars, cafes and restaurants all less than a 5 minute walk away.
 
Features in the apartment include -
 
Split system heating/cooling
Dishwasher
Washing Machine
Dryer
Microwave 
Full kitchen facilities
Wireless Internet
42 inch flat screen LCD TV
Large and immaculately clean bathroom
Queen size bed and built in double robes
Balcony with outdoor setting
 
Only 2.5kms from Melbourne's CBD and a short tram trip to the MCG and sporting precinct. It's an ideal place to come home to, away from the hustle and bustle and noise of the city.

Yuri
