host_about:
Hi my name is Dawei, I started doing Airbnb September 2015. 

I'm a 20 years old undergraduate student currently studying commercial law. I like to watch movies and play video games. Sometimes I could spend my whole day in my room just play games. I thought that there isn't much things to do outside and I thought the World was a boring place. When I'm not playing games, I would read news on the internet just to catch up with the rest of the world. That's how I knew Airbnb. 

One day, my father come to me, talked about doing short term renting. He has got few new apartments that our relatives bought which needs to be rented out. I told him about Airbnb and he thought we could really make it work. So I asked my best friend if he is interested to be my partner for this, and he said yes. We started almost immediately, planning, buying furnitures to started taking guests in just two weeks. 

Then it really changed me.

I met with travellers around the world. Every body was so polite and friendly.  When I talk to them I can feel the excitement and happiness. It's totally  different compare to what I thought people are like. Maybe because this communicate is great, I don't know.  Then I  thought "I want to be people like my guests". I want people around me to feel life is great and there are a lot to look forward to. The guests really gave me a lot motivation towards my work and my life. Here I have to thank you all.

After one month, the revenue was great, however take away the interests and loans, all kinds of fees and salary for my partner, there are really not much left for me. But I think that's enough, I'm still a student, I have to spend time on study and don't have much things to spend money on anyway, being able to save money for a holiday with my girl friend every few month is perfect for me. 

After all these experience, I felt it really changed my life and how I view the world. Doesn't matter if I fail or succeed it's  going to effect the rest of my life in a very positive way, that's something really valuable to me.

Hi! My name is Paul, owner of Complete Host apartments! I am an avid traveller (Ive visited more than 55 countries and counting) and enjoy soaking in cultures from all parts of the world whenever i get the opportunity.

When in Melbourne I run a unique short stay apartment business that i am so fortunate to call my day job. I love meeting and hosting guests and doing my best to enhance their Melbourne experience. I do have a small team behind me so it may not always be me you hear from. 

I am very proud to have been named an AIRBNB Superhost for a couple of years now. What does that mean to you? I have never cancelled a guest's  booking and close to 90% of the reviews we receive are rated 5 stars by our guests. You can be confident if you book a property with us firstly the keys will always be there when you turn up and we will do everything we can to ensure you have a wonderful stay.

If you are interested in one of the properties l have listed but the dates are unavailable, please check my other listings or email me an enquiry as l will very likely have another property available that will suit your requirements. 

I can't wait to host you or meet you soon!

Paul, Complete Host

summary: Eat breakfast at the aqua bistro table in the tropical backyard at a trendy, listed loft in one of the city's trendiest suburbs. This hip pad features an open-air bedroom, a sleek, white breakfast bar, and pops of rich teal and zesty yellow.
space: This private and secluded 2 bedroom / 2 bathroom stylish warehouse is situated in an iconic heritage listed pharmacist laboratory. Positioned adjacent to Smith Street, with Brunswick Street and Gertrude Street only a short stroll away. You will be entering a Foodie's Paradise, staying amongst some of the best restaurants and cafe's that Melbourne has to offer! This space is perfect for couples, business travellers and families (with kids). A secure car park in a garage is also included. This two bedroom / two bathroom Collingwood warehouse is unique and spectacularly located. A one minute walk and you will be standing in the centre of Smith Street. The downstairs bedroom has bifold doors which can be closed for privacy however the upstairs loft bedroom is open to the property and does not have doors. Each bedroom has its own ensuite including separate showers. Features * Beautifully secluded courtyard with gorgeous tropical plants * Heating / air-conditioning that warms the entire prop
host_about:
G'day!

Mybnb here and it's nice to meet you! We look after multiple properties throughout Melbourne. We're a complete management solution, meaning we take care of absolutely everything. From creating your listing to having you place cleaned, we do it all! 

Whilst managing properties through Airbnb, we've learnt a lot about the various areas and different nuances Melbourne has to offer. On top of that, we love meeting honest, genuine and interesting guests, some of whom have become friends too!

Living in the sporting and cultural hub of Australia has it's perks. It's a great city to visit and an even better one to live in. We look forward to sharing it with you!

See you soon :-)

Blake (Mybnb)

name: ★ Fresh Fitzroy Pad with City Views! ★
summary: Modern, spacious and fresh! This magnificent apartment with city views is situated in the heart of Fitzroy's bustling scene of unique culture, entertainment, food, bars, parks and activities.  Featuring a large balcony, this is the PERFECT pad to settle in and explore. Live in absolute comfort and enjoy special company while exploring the best of what Melbourne has to offer! Relax, unwind and enjoy!
space: This Fitzroy apartment is the perfect place to live and relax, with a comfortable queen bed and modern facilities. Modern, clean, spacious and with a private balcony, It has everything you need to enjoy a long or short term stay.  For new visitors to Melbourne, this place serves as a perfect hub to explore the city, while as a returning visitor this is the perfect home away from home, featuring everything you need. The kitchen is fully equipped with large fridge, dishwasher, microwave, oven and stove. All cooking utensils are provided as well the essentials to whip up a 5-star meal. The bathroom is modern and clean with shampoo, conditioner, soap and hairdryer provided. There is also a washer, dryer and a drying rack. Apart from this being a great apartment with its amenities and décor, the location is AMAZING!
host_about:
G'day,

I'm Joel, i'm born and raised in Sydney, which is in my opinion one of the most beautiful major cities in the world. My goal in life is to one day visit every country in the world, I hold no bias to any of them and hope that I get the opportunity. So far I have visited 42 countries. Last year I spent 1 year travelling in South and Central America and loved the opportunity I had to learn Spanish. It was a great experience and one that I will never forget. 

My hobbies include all forms of board sports, skating, surfing and snowboarding primarily. I enjoy learning about new cultures especially their foods. I grew up in an Italian restaurant so my love for food and cooking is deeply engrained in my personality. 

My style of hosting and living life in general is pretty relaxed. I will do my best to greet you at the door and make your stay as enjoyable as possible. But if you just want to chill I can totally relate. 

I also love music and watching live music. I mostly go out to see House, deep house and techno music as that scene in Sydney is easily accessible. However at home you will find me listening to hip-hop, reggae, latin, afro-beat, jazz and anything with a smooth and funky beat. 

If you need recommendations about food or music in Sydney these are probably my two strongest topics, so please don't hesitate. 

Looking forward to meeting more crazy, fun and cool people through Airbnb. 

Joel

I'm a coffee, wine and food fanatic from Melbourne Australia. I'm a Superhost who's lived my entire life - more than half a century and counting - in Melbourne near the city along the bay. Additionally I travel regularly - at least a couple of times a year to Asia and Europe. When I travel I stay in airbnb's and I've come to understand what it is that makes a great stay - or a bad one. Now I strive to replicate the very best of my own travel accommodation experiences.
When you stay in one of my places you can expect:

*   To be met at - or within 12 hours of - arrival

space: Welcome to a creative space, nestled in East Melbourne, close to everything that this great city has to offer. Full of character, this ground floor apartment is set in a lovely 1920's block. This heritage property is full of charm and grace. The space is adorned with local artworks and filled with indoor plants, making for a tranquil getaway. We offer a large room with wardrobe, lots of hanging space and storage, a comfortable double bed with designer linen and fresh towels. It is your haven of uncluttered calm, filled with greenery, looking onto a secluded walled succulent and herb garden. You will be very close to the city attractions, but tucked away from the hustle and bustle, in this comfortable and well-equipped apartment. The home is well lived in and full of quirky charm, creaky floors and light filled spaces. Not a 5 star hotel but a stunning way to visits Melbourne in a heritage building.  It is a 5 minute walk to the MCG, 10 minutes to Rod Laver Arena, Richmond is just aroun
host_about: Hey, we are Andrew and Tom, your hosts. Originally from Australia, we have relocated to the UK in 2018. Andrew works as a researcher and podcaster in the Arts, studying male dancers and connecting communities. Tom is an actor and performance artist who has a great love of theatre and film. We have been through Eastern Europe, Iceland, UK, the US (NYC, LA, San Fran, etc.) Japan, Fiji, New Zealand, India, Germany, Turkey, Vietnam, Cambodia, Thailand and other places along the way. We love cooking and good food (and an occasional great wine). We eat mostly Vegetarian and love a well brewed coffee. We both have a strong love of the arts, with theatre, dance and performance art being some of our strongest passions. As much as we love living in the city, we have a deep appreciation of the bush (or woods, depending where you come from) and being surrounded by nature, be it a nice garden, a secluded beach or lost in the middle of a national park. So much more, lets have a tea and a chat!

host_about:
G'day,

I'm Joel, i'm born and raised in Sydney, which is in my opinion one of the most beautiful major cities in the world. My goal in life is to one day visit every country in the world, I hold no bias to any of them and hope that I get the opportunity. So far I have visited 42 countries. Last year I spent 1 year travelling in South and Central America and loved the opportunity I had to learn Spanish. It was a great experience and one that I will never forget. 

My hobbies include all forms of board sports, skating, surfing and snowboarding primarily. I enjoy learning about new cultures especially their foods. I grew up in an Italian restaurant so my love for food and cooking is deeply engrained in my personality. 

My style of hosting and living life in general is pretty relaxed. I will do my best to greet you at the door and make your stay as enjoyable as possible. But if you just want to chill I can totally relate. 

I also love music and watching live music. I mostly go out to see House, deep house and techno music as that scene in Sydney is easily accessible. However at home you will find me listening to hip-hop, reggae, latin, afro-beat, jazz and anything with a smooth and funky beat. 

If you need recommendations about food or music in Sydney these are probably my two strongest topics, so please don't hesitate. 

Looking forward to meeting more crazy, fun and cool people through Airbnb. 

Joel

I've since become an avid traveller that has journeyed across the globe. Meeting new people, discovering new foods, embracing new cultures - it's something I'd never get sick of.

I also have a team of 5-Star luxury vehicle drivers. We can pick up / drop off 24 - 7 - 365. We offer fully catered day trips on request ( wineries , great ocean road, hot springs, event drop off / collection ). 

Throughout my professional life, i have been one to travel quite a lot - and know the importance of a safe, comfortable place to relax and unwind. Thanks for checking out my profile, hope to share my spaces with you soon! 

TOP 5 THINGS TO DO IN SOUTHBANK:

1)     NGV - what more can i say? Amazing place! 
2)    Melbourne Arts Centre - the Eiffel tower of Aus!
3)    Convention Centre - this is where the Terminator himself hosts his annual event. The " Arnold Classic ". - You will be back ( there is also chopper rides ). 
4)    Eureka Skydeck 88.  297m high. You may need a drink following the experience. 
5)    PonyFish Island Bar. Cool spot for a Gin and Tonic. 

Look forward to speaking to you! 

- Nate

Wall-sized glass sliding doors lead to a covered, generously sized balcony with an outdoor sofa, overlooking Melbourne’s Yarra River and the Crown Entertainment complex. host_about:
Hey, I’m Aymeric!

I’m a French expat from the vineyards of Bordeaux with a love for animals and traveling. At 18, I moved to the USA for 10 years and lived in Boston, Miami Beach and San Francisco while exploring most of Canada, Central and South America. For the past 15 years I’ve lived in Sydney, Australia, mainly because of the beautiful beaches here. On weekends in summer, you can find me volunteering as a surf lifesaver on Tamarama beach.

I work for MaisonNets, a boutique agency specializing in short-term rental management. The MaisonNets portfolio has over 125 properties, encompassing mid-range to luxury apartments and houses in Australia’s capital cities, as well as country homes and a villa in Bali.  

Our properties are all specifically selected for their amenities and prime location - the accommodation of choice for urban sophisticates, professionals, couples and families looking for a uniquely comfortable experience.

With a focus on organic products, MaisonNets offers unparalleled personal service and attention to detail ensuring that you, our valued guest, have a wonderful stay with us.

host_about:
Melbourne, Australia is my adopted city and country.  It's home. 

Born in the USA,  my family moved to Germany at a young age where we stayed for nine years before moving to Australia when I was in my early teens. 

I have experience in hospitality having worked full time for two years as Concierge in one of Melbourne's 5 star hotels. 

My husband was also born overseas - in Bucharest, Romania.  
After escaping the former communist regime, he lived in both Germany and France before finally settling in Australia in his early 20's. 

Both of us, having lived in many different countries as well as having traveled a bit, love exploring and experiencing a new place.  We also appreciate the importance what a great location and amenity can offer when visiting a place for a while or a short time. 

Between us we can speak 5 languages - English, German, Romanian, French and Italian to varying levels of ability, if it helps you out. 

We hope you book in and enjoy your stay in our cool apartment and get to love our adopted city of Melbourne as much as we do.

Both of us are rowing Commonwealth Games Gold and Olympic Bronze medalists - ironically.....for Australia.   

Rowing is still very much part of our lives.  We're very active in the local rowing community and operate the only private rowing school in Australia called Rowing School Victoria - it's been located on the stunning Yarra River since 2007.    We love it.

We're generally up and about or nearby the apartment.  We spend quite a bit of time coaching our rowing students as we ride our bikes alongside them on the stretch of river that runs from Princes Bridge in the City, to just past Chapel Street, South Yarra.    

We'll be easily available via mobile, email, text or in person if needed.

This CLEAN, STYLISH house has luxuries including heating/cooling, fireplace, Nespresso machine, dishwasher, bathtub, wifi with Netflix, complimentary breakfast supplies, etc.
space: Large open living area include a dining room seating eight people, living room with jetmaster fireplace and large kitchen with everything you’ll need.  There are 3 bright and beautiful Bedrooms, including one King Master bedroom, one Queen double bedroom and a king single. Linen and bath towels supplied. Next to the kitchen is a large walk-in laundry equipped with washing machine and a clothes horse to hang washing. Under the sink, cleaning products are provided.  Tall bamboo and lush succulents line the sunny courtyard at the back of the property. Open the back doors to create a villa-like feeling, perfect for summer. There is an electric awning, operated via remote to provide shade over the entire courtyard. The BBQ is connected to house gas line. The house is equipped with a Hydronic Heating system and gas Jetmaster fireplace for cooler months and an Evaporative Cooling system for use in summer.
host_about:
My husband & I have enjoyed raising our 3 children in Bayside Brighton and now they have all grown up, we are loving spending more time in nature and travelling.  As my work is more part time these days, I can spend lovely time with friends,  going to see live theatre and spending time on our farm.

I have had some wonderful experiences with Airbnb whilst travelling  and I'm now excited to start hosting.

summary: Live the high life in this brand new, spacious apartment 29 floors up in the heart of Melbourne! A fully furnished 2 bedroom and 1 bathroom with high quality appliances awaits you. space: The apartment itself provides access to a brand new, state of the art gym with snooker table and table tennis. The location cannot be beaten for convenience with literally an Asian grocery downstairs, Aldi around the corner, free zone tram stops at the doorstep and RMIT on the same block. Chinatown is a short 5 min walk, Melbourne central is even closer. University of Melbourne is a 5 min tram ride away. Not to mention Victoria Market and all the shops and restaurants of Elizabeth street.
host_about:
We are not Real Estate Agents. 

We are home owners. Our properties are owned by local Australians who are working hard to pay their mortgages and are willing to share their treasured homes with guests from all over the world. This means that we genuinely care about the properties we offer and the services that are available to guests during their stay.

We are accommodating. Regardless of the purpose of your stay, be it for work, a family holiday, a relaxing vacation, a school tour, a family gathering or a special occasion, we love to welcome people to our properties and we always aim to go above and beyond to ensure that your stay is memorable. We will be the first to offer you a safe place to stay should your home be affected by natural causes or if you are waiting for building to be completed. We can accommodate your group no matter the occasion and our homes are the perfect place for you to make unforgettable memories.

We are caring. We cherish our properties, tending to them regularly and treating them like they are our family members. Each property has a unique character and story to tell and we love that we can offer so many diverse homes for our guests to enjoy. Whether you're looking for a slice of history, a unique shape or an out-of-this-world location, we have something to suit every occasion and budget.

We are respectful. We pride ourselves on the 5-Star experience that is offered to all guests from the time of booking right through to your departure. You can expect open communication throughout but we will always respect your privacy and allow you to enjoy your stay. We ask that you are also respectful of our properties, understanding that not every listing is a 5-Star luxury hotel with concierge service but a wonderful space for you to feel at home.

We are good listeners. We support, update, improve and look after our properties to the highest standards and we love to make improvements wherever we can. While we cannot remove the noisy traffic in the CBD or the rocky roads in rural areas, we will always aim to do our best to ensure that your stay is as pleasant as possible. Please let us know if there is anything that we can improve on.

We are welcoming. We welcome all of our valued guests with care and we love being the reason that your trip was faultless. The walls of our homes are filled with the stories and memories of so many people and we hope that we can offer you the perfect place to make memories of your own. 

Why are we not Estate Agents? Because we are so much more.

space: Our house is a fantastic, typical 'hills' home. It's quirky, split level and retro. The room available is large, dark and cosy with an outlook into the trees. We still love  traveling, although our overseas trips have become family friendly local jaunts.

I am studying and and working part time whilst Rowan spends a lot of time working outside with a new found love of gardening. Tom is a typical toddler. He's upbeat, noisey and charming all at the same time. He is used to being around lots of different people.

host_about:
Mornington Peninsula Holiday Accommodation (MPHA) is located on the Mornington Peninsula approximately one hour south east of Melbourne in Victoria Australia.
We manage holiday properties all over the Peninsula, helping thousands of people every year with their family holidays, sports trips, romantic getaways and business conferences. Our aim is to make the holidays of our clients as memorable as possible, providing advice on where to stay, play and eat.
The Mornington Peninsula is a popular place for tourists to visit and currently, over 2 million people visit the Peninsula every year. There are many fabulous things to experience besides the stunning beaches, such as world class golf courses, outstanding wineries, luxurious day spas, magnificent scuba diving, fishing charters and horse riding, to name just a few.

space: The house itself is very large and open, with high ceilings, a large kitchen and is heated throughout. The house is quite old and very quirky (which is what we love about it!). The upstairs area, as we call it - your domain - is a really big and bright space that has views of the trees and park across the road. The bathroom has also been renovated and has a bath as well as a shower.  We've kitted out your space with a new bar fridge, a toaster, kettle and some snacks as well! There is plenty of space to store your luggage and clothes in the built-in wardrobes.  A new and very sexy Samsung smart-tv compliments the space and has complete access to Netflix, our surround sound dvd system and the wider internet of course.  There is a door to the stairway that you can keep closed when you feel like some privacy. We are just looking to meet new and interesting people from other places, but we understand the need for privacy and some quiet when it's asked for as well!
host_about:
Hi there, my name is Jeremy and I'm the host of two very different listings. The first is my own home, which I share with my friendly (and thoroughly international roommates). The second is my parents very new and entirely awesome holiday home by the sea! 

I've been hosting for over 3 years now and it's been a great experience - I've met some truly unique and lovely people and it's been a real privilege to be able to show so many people how fantastic both Melbourne and Ocean Grove can be. From the big city to the golden sands and exciting surf down the coast - I get to show off everything that Victoria has to offer. 

I'm always available for a chat, so please don't hesitate to message me or give me a buzz if you have any questions or concerns.

This is my small business which I  run more  from heart than mind. You don't have to look at the watch before contacting me. I will try my best to make sure that you have a  great stay in one of my apartment.

host_about:

I work in the health and wellbeing sector and believe in living life consciously, lightly and with purpose. I enjoy going for walks or riding my bike along our beautiful river, park and beach-side tracks; I do yoga, meditate, paint and dance latin (all with varying degrees of success :) I also like attending live music events, theatres, galleries, eating out and meeting great people, all of which I can enjoy in this great city of ours. So it gives me great pleasure to think that your stay in my apartment may in some small way enhance your experience of Melbourne, contribute to precious memories of your time here, and that you will want to return!

Hi I'm Jackie and am the owner and manager of Allara House, in Victoria's gorgeous Yarra Valley region.  

Allara House was purpose-built in late 2014 as a boutique self-contained accommodation option,  within walking distance of the township of Healesville.  My husband and I set out to create a home that guests from Australia and around the world could enjoy during their time in the Yarra Valley.  As a self-confessed clean freak, I get great pleasure out of ensuring every room is of a very high standard of cleanliness (can you tell I'm a Virgo also!)

Since our opening in October 2014, we have been humbled by the amazing guests from Australia-wide and overseas, all of whom have commented on the high standard of cleanliness and facilities of Allara House. We have also had many wedding parties use the home as their base for their wedding day in the Yarra Valley. 

I look forward to hearing from you and hope to be able to accommodate you at Allara House for either a short or longer stay.  

Best wishes and happy travels,
Jackie

host_about:
Hi from Bronnie and Neil ;-)
We love being airbnb hosts and sharing our homes and our beautiful city with others.
We have been airbnb hosts for over four years and during that time we have met amazing and wonderful people from all around Australia and all parts of the world.
We started with the spare room in our own home and now have 20 properties, from high end luxury to family friendly apartments that we offer our guests. We even have a 7 bedroom, 7 bathroom mansion near the sea in St Kilda for larger groups! 
We use airbnb ourselves whenever we travel and feel we know what people are looking for. Good value, great locations, clean, comfortable and friendly! All our properties are in great locations, are professionally cleaned and we use hotel quality, commercially laundered linen on comfortable beds.  We meet all our guests on arrival to say hello and are on hand to offer help, advice and inside tips of places to go and things to see. 
Most of our properties include free parking which is a real bonus in the city and Foxtel (cable) television and other homely touches so you 'can live like a local'. (You can view our properties by clicking the View Full Profile link below and clicking on the listings on the left hand side of the page). 

A little bit about ourselves ... we're pretty easy going, and love getting out and about exploring different places. We are both keen travellers and have done our fair share of it in Australia and overseas - whether backpacking, camping, or an occasional splurge on 5-star resorts! You wouldn't call us 'party animals', but we do like socialising and meeting people.  We enjoy a wide variety of interests, love the movies, eating out, popping down to the beach on our scooter or pushbikes, and enjoying the many exciting sporting events and festivals that Melbourne has to offer.
Our motto is "strangers are just friends you haven't met yet!"
Wishing you happy travels and looking forward to meeting you soon :-)

Best regards
Bronnie and Neil

host_about:
Hi there,

Approximately 10% of all my airbnb fee's go to Kiva to help reduce poverty and enable some of the poorest, hard working people in the world.  Check them out on the web.  I'll be happy to link with you personally on this if you would like to know more.  More below if you are interested.

I love where I live, the neighbourhood, good restaurants are plenty as well as Hot Yoga and Pilates and lots of delightful walks to take through the surrounding parks. The antics of my animals keeps me amused around the house.  

My most recent travel destination was a hike to Mt Everest Base camp with my wonderful son who is traveling the globe again at the moment.

I've had some delightful guests to host - all just wonderful, decent and interesting people from all walks of life.  I like my guests to settle in and feel comfortable and at home.

I'm a professional person in the IT industry and lead a pretty hectic lifestyle, but look forward to meeting some wonderful people who I might visit in return around the globe.

I like to keep fit and am getting back into my fitness, pilates classes and enjoy hot yoga. :)  

I've ticked "German" below as I do speak a little.  My grammar is often amusing though .... apparently!

Hope to host you soon and enjoy a chat.  Cheers N..

Now about Kiva....

A non-profit organization with a mission to connect people through lending to alleviate poverty. Leveraging the internet and a worldwide network of microfinance institutions, Kiva lets individuals lend as little as $25 to help create opportunity around the world. Learn more about how it works.

Since Kiva was founded in (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) :

They have over 1.2 million Kiva lenders
$ (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) in loans (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) % repayment rate

Why Kiva ..

We envision a world where all people - even in the most remote areas of the globe - hold the power to create opportunity for themselves and others.

We believe providing safe, affordable access to capital to those in need helps people create better lives for themselves and their families.

How we do it

Making a loan on Kiva is so simple that you may not realize how much work goes on behind the scenes.

Kiva works with microfinance institutions on five continents to provide loans to people without access to traditional banking systems. One hundred percent of your loan is sent to these microfinance institutions, which we call Field Partners, who administer the loans in the field.

How we're funded

100% of every dollar you lend on Kiva goes directly towards funding loans; Kiva does not take a cut. Furthermore, Kiva does not charge interest to our Field Partners, who administer the loans.

host_about: I am a hard working person and enjoy communicating with anyone and everyone. I love being an Airbnb host as it gives me a chance to help others and provide exceptional service. I love helping people make money and I experimented on my own apartment with Airbnb. It's been empty 27 days in 4 years. I now have 16 under Airbnb. They are properties that I have bought for investors (I'm a buyers advocate) and for landlords who wanted (needed) to double their incomes.  I take a budget and I purchase all the furnishing down to the potato peeler,  accept the deliveries, set it up, wash the towels, take the photographs and then list it on Airbnb. My motto is "We do everything for you except pay for it and move in." As the short stay business has grown let me introduce Motaz Alamarat. Motaz is my colleague and was head of "front of house" at a 5 star resort in Jordan. He is the most gorgeous young man and his mind set is completely focused on ensuring all our guests have an enjoyable experience. Most of the time Motaz will meet and greet our guests any time day or night. I help out where needed. He will ensure that the apartment is clean and everything is working on your arrival. We look to ensure our landlord's property achieves a 4.8 star score.

Restaurant strip nearby.  Relaxing garden space.   On street parking.  Close to M1 Monash Freeway. Near the fabulous Chadstone Shopping Centre and the Oakleigh Mall eateries.
space: Spacious living areas define this house, and there is heaps of room to relax outside in the garden. There is a Nespresso coffee machine for guest use. Fridge space for visitor use.
host_about:
I am an active person, and a keen cyclist.
I enjoy the outdoors, growing plants, and exploring.
Melbourne is a cobweb of green, made up of parks, waterways, and reserves. Most of these have a cycling path running alongside or through it.
I also speak passable german.

summary: Beautifully renovated art deco family  home nestled in a quiet leafy tree lined street, sleeps 8.Close to public transport with easy access to St Kilda Beach, Melbourne CBD,  Prahran, Malvern, Toorak, Balaclava,Chapel St, Glenferrie & Ackland  Streets. Parking is available outside our home in this quiet residential street.  A leisurely short walk to Caulfield Park and  great cafes and restaurants. All Melbourne has to offer is within easy reach by public transport or walking. Outdoor deck, BBQ
space: A beautiful character home freshly renovated with a rear private garden with sunny outdoor deck & pergola for chilling out sun-baking or snoozing.  Meticulously-presented and maintained with contemporary furnishings and decor. A perfect getaway in an inner city location for friends, execs and families alike.  This home is filled with natural light throughout with double doors leading from the kitchen to a sunny deck. Enjoy a meal on the deck or lay back and enjoy the sun relaxing in a sun lounge.  Free street parking for multiple cars. We are located in close reach of freeways - M1 / Princes Highway. We are in a great safe quiet neighbourhood with easy access to city/beach and shopping precincts of Chapel street, Ackland street, High Street & Glenferrie streets. Public transport by Trams or buses right at the door step. The train station is 5min by tram or a 15 minute walk. St Kilda/Beach 10 mins by tram; City 12 Mins by train; MCG 10 Mins by Train. The main bedroom has a king bed, and
host_about: Unknown

name: The heart of vibrant Fitzroy
summary: Located in popular Fitzroy, experience inner suburb living a stones throw from seriously great coffee, bars, street art, galleries and shopping. In Melbourne its the inner suburbs, not the CBD that are the place to be.
space: Chilled out central location, origional artwork and a relaxed atmosphere with a mindful, intiutive host who has made Melbourne home. More photos to come! Wireless, Kitchen, Balcony, shared bathroom, laundry. If I'm home I enjoy getting to know my guests, if you enjoy this aspect of travel (otherwise I can leave to your own devices!). I love connecting with new and interesting people and sharing my coffee/music/bar tips.  Fitzroy is a central, chilled out area with plenty of character. It has many cafes, bars and a rich music scene. Away from the hustle and bustle of the CBD you'll find street art galore and plenty to stimulate your mind in terms of small galleries and loads of interesting stores to peruse. Very close to tram 11 and 96 (goes direct to the sky bus). Short walk to Melbourne Museum. I'm able to speak Swedish if required.
host_about: Well travelled, chilled out science geek often found on dance floors. Interests include meeting genuine people, reading a good book in a cafe, nutrition, wellness and meditation.

name: Paradise Location 3BD in Southbank
summary: Our spacious, modern and dynamic 3BD apartment is placed in the heart of Melbourne's Southbank district. It is a quite residential complex, offering pool, gym, and space. Access to city, sports and arts venues, and the best restaurants and bars.
space: The apartment is perfect, everyone says that it feels like a home away from home.  Only minutes from Southgate River Promenade, Crown Casino, the Arts Centre, Botanical Gardens or the CBD, boasting great coffee, amazing breakfast, world class eateries, a river escapade, or the many arts and gardens.  Only 10 minute walk from Melbourne's sporting hub, the MCG, the Australian Open tennis centre, AAMI stadium (home of ARL rugby and A League soccer), and Etihad Stadium.  It is a short drive to the beaches, and the famous, ultra hip, cool strips of Chapel Street (Cool), Acland Street (Hip), Brunswick St (Alternative), and Lygon St (Italian). Tram stop is a minute way. Train: Melbourne's famous and central Flinders street station is across the river, 7 minute walk. Taxi's are always passing by on the main streets. With car, you are a block away from the freeway that can take you east west south or north. Secure parking on site. This place is not your 30 storey building where you feel trapped
host_about:
I love Australian football (AFL), cricket, and most other sports. Good food and great restaurants, a new beer and even a good cocktail. Travelling is a must, and good music be it current or old school.

Family first, everything second.

My motto is "Life is not a rehearsal".

Very genuine person, approachable, love having a laugh and always see the good in things.

As a host I go out of my way to ensure a great stay.

name: Stylish central apartment with views
summary: Stylish designer-furnished 2-bedroom 2-bathroom apartment in the Lacrosse / M Docklands twin towers located between CBD and Docklands. Wolking distance to Southern cross station and skybus, shopping centers, CBD, Etihad stadium, Docklands, tram (free tram zone).
space: WHAT: Entire apartment with interior design by Italian designer Pietro Russomanno ( (Website hidden by Airbnb) This is a 2 bedroom 2 bathroom flat (one bedroom has ensuite toilet). The flat is furnished to a high standard and features, among other appliances (such as washing machine, microwave, dishwasher, oven etc), a 60" apple TV (JVC) and Nespresso coffee machine. Stunning views from the generous balcony featuring outdoor lounge set. Free use of gym and swimming pool. WHERE: This flat is in the perfect location. Five minutes walk to Southern cross station, the CBD, Docklands, tram at you doorstep (free tram zone).

The well appointed stone benchtop kitchen with stainless steel 4 burner hob gas cooktops, oven, dishwasher and microwave allows you to engage with guests or family whilst entertaining. Wake up to a fresh coffee from your very own espresso pod coffee machine and enjoy breakfast whilst reading a newspaper sitting on your private terrace with a 6 person outdoor dining table and 2 lounge chairs. The spacious master bedroom includes a luxurious 5 star hotel quality king size bed, private ensuite bathroom and built in robes. A laptop friendly work desk is included in the master bedroom for business travellers.   A private terrace off the master bedroom is also available with your own private 2 person dining table. An additional bedroom with built in robes contains a 5 star hotel quality king
host_about:

We are a professional short & long stay property management team, which means you can book with complete confidence for a stress-free stay during your visit! 

We're always here to help you find your way around Melbourne. Do not hesitate to get in touch for further information.

It is in the back end of a small complex of 12 apartments, with only 6 using our entrance which means you don’t get disturbed by any foot traffic. It also requires you to come through a security door for added safety.

Close to restaurants, cafes, 12 min to Austin hospitals, 14 km to CBD and 2 min walk to tram & bus stop. Walk to shopping centers.

We are a convenient location to be near to Bacchus Marsh and Melton facilities but much quieter and more serene. If you are attending a wedding and/or reception at the Eynesbury Homestead, we are walking distance from the venue.
space: Comfortable beds and quiet surroundings to relax in. Rush-free suburb with lovely old Eynesbury Homestead at its heart... great for a drink ( hot or cold), a meal or just a snack. Maybe take up the chance for a round of golf on the beautiful 18 hole PGA rated course.

Registered Nurse who works full time, teaching first aid for a private provider in Melbourne.
Hockey umpire of many years and happily partnered to Mark Bentley nearly 8 years now and we have two furbaby Border Collies. Scooby and Bella.
Mark is a concierge at a National Data Storage Company located in The Docklands.

name: Live your own Upper West Side story.
summary: The building is conveniently located @ 280 Spencer Street on the corner of Little Lonsdale Street. You have a free tram stop on your doorstep and Melbourne's largest train station across the street. Melbourne is Australia’s most exciting and rapidly developing city! So there is often construction around the city-centre which can be a little bit noisy for some people at times. However, the food, the sights, the vibe and the friendly people more than make up for any construction noise :)
space: To stay in theme with the airbnb culture, I aim to be 100% open, honest and transparent with all guests. My studio apartment is not a 6 star penthouse, nor is it a 1 star budget motel either. Its somewhere in between. My cozy little studio is clean, neat, basic and comfortable with some 5 star touches like hair dryer, hair straighter, unique artwork and breathtaking, panoramic views from the rooftop pool. What makes it attractive is its prime location and simplicity. If you’re looking for super fancy accommodation on the high end, or perhaps something super cheap on the low-end, then my place is probably not for you. But if you’re looking for accommodation that is decent, basic, clean, neat and comfortable with a few stylish perks and surprises, then my apartment is definitely for you. Unbeatable location and breathtaking ocean and city views from the rooftop pool make this place a unique and authentic Melbourne experience.
host_about: I love to travel and try new food. I love my home town of Melbourne but I really enjoy experiencing europe and asia.

name: Spacious bedroom with shared  facilities
summary: Welcoming you to the the guest room. This spacious and sunlit room comes equipped with a queen size bed, desk, wardobe and multiple storage spaces. Public areas include dining, kitchen and laundry areas.
space: Hello to all, we are listing a spacious and sunlit room equipped with a queen size bed, desk, wardobe and multiple storage spaces to let in Seaford for long and short term stays. We are conveniently close to shops and malls, schools, bike and walking trails, the beach which is only a 5 minute drive and the bus stop only a minute walk. You will have your own room that includes free wifi. Public areas include dining, kitchen and laundry areas. Laundry area is at no cost provided you use your own washing detergent.
host_about:
Greetings world, 
My name is Peter and I welcome you all to my own special place here in Seaford :) 
When I hear Seaford the first thing that comes to my mind is "home". I've resided here for most of my life and can freely say it's a good and fun place to stay at. Seaford is home to a magnificent beach which spans across the mornington peninsula. The views are breathtaking, the people are welcoming and there are so many outdoor activities and places to visit to keep yourself busy. 
I also have a career in nursing and the sector I work in is rehabilitation. I have a strong commitment to property development as my goal in life is to be financially free through property. Through this I hope to travel every country, meet new people and do my bid to make the world a better place :)

summary: A true haven in Heidelberg, this house is located on a quiet no-through road, just a short walk from the Austin, Mercy and Warringal hospitals, and a short drive from the Repatriation Hospital. With the vibrant café culture of Burgundy Street on your doorstep, the perfect coffee, lunch or dinner is just a stroll away. Free WIFI, bed linen, towels and some basic consumables are provided.
space: This modern three-bedroom, two-bathroom home can effortlessly accommodate up to seven guests, while the three living zones and serene landscaped rear garden give you all the space you will need. Instant hot water and ducted heating/cooling further ensure your comfort, while the driveway provides parking for your vehicle in addition to on-street parking.
host_about:
Professional, humour-loving, caring, can't live without laughter, family & friends. 
Love to travel, read, watch movies, entertain (incl. home baking), crafts & knitting & live each day as it comes.

My Haven is 'your home away from home', where you can relax and enjoy the surrounds.

name: 2 bed modern apartment in Melbourne CBD
summary: Modern apartment in good condition, on 2nd floor. One bedroom which has a futon couch- folds out to a single bed. Main living area has queen bed, kitchen, dining table, couch, desk (stand or sit). One large window, not much of a view but you can see the sky and you get natural light. Polished wooden floors. Security entrance to building. Stairs or lift access. People from all backgrounds are welcome.
space: Old style building, built in 1908, but apartment is modern.
host_about:
I am a Feldenkrais movement therapist and teacher, offering one-to-ones, classes and workshops here in Melbourne and around the world.
I love to dance, mostly 5 Rhythms and Contact Improv. Love reading, many styles of music, choir singing, time with friends and family, cricket (playing and watching), bicycling. I care about our natural environment and encourage/support animal welfare and sustainable living locally and globally. I care about human rights and justice and support equal rights and opportunities for all.
Single. 3 adult children (who will do some helping me with hosting).
In a happy stage of life, in good, active health, enjoying my work and play.

Lauren and I are both professionals in our late 20's. I am a social worker and Lauren is an art therapist.

name: Aye...cityViews...topFloor...private...

Near to parkland, zoo, hospitals, universities, and Melbourne CBD. Great cafe's and laundry across the road, shops nearby: grocery, pharmacy, wine, nuts, bread, restaurants, take-away food. The longer you stay, the cheaper it gets !!!
space: The whole apartment is yours to stay in. It offers private comfortable accomodation, more homely than a hotel, motel or hostel. Some guests stay for a couple of days, but most stay for a few weeks, or months. It is completely set up with what you will need: linen, towels, crockery, pots and pans, and includes electricity, gas and other outgoings. It might suit those who come to visit family or friends, have arrived for a new job, doing a semester at University (lecturing or studying), those in Melbourne for horse-race events, festivals, or on holiday. The digital television has a USB port, DVD player and remote control. Public transport, car hire and shops are very conveniently located.
host_about:
I am self-employed, working with plants and people, and love what I do. I also love to travel, explore new places, and meet different people.  I have stayed in other peoples homes all over the world and generally find it nicer than hotels and motels, though I have come across some doozies...exampling what not to do as a host, and have taken note ! 
I love hosting visitors and sharing my space and I do my utmost to make my place comfortable and suited to your needs.
Boating is a constant wonderful theme in my life, and roughing it in a swag by the river also comes quite easy to me. So perhaps while you are staying in my place, I might be on or beside the water somewhere....

name: A winning place to stay
summary: Conveniently close to buses, trams, trains and the many attractions Melbourne offers. Your own large room, access to a balcony, use of laundry and kitchen facilities. Newly renovated throughout with off-street parking. Relaxed, friendly, fun host.
space: The apartment has been recently renovated. The oven is new and the flat screen tv great for watching sport. It's a pleasure to come home, relax and recuperate and then head out for a coffee or dinner at one of the nearby cafes or head to the park . And there is wifi.
host_about: Friendly, relaxed, easy-going. Fit and healthy and always on the go. Aiming to ensure you have a terrific experience so that you'll love to come back and share your experience with your friends and family.

summary: ,     - Including fast wifi - 15 mins away by Uber from the Melbourne airport     - 25 mins to the CBD by train - 15 mins walk to Albion station/ pickup or drop off can be arranged - 5 mins walk to 903 and 408 bus stops, which goes to Sunshine or Ginnifer station - Security lock on bedroom door - Great restaurants nearby, especially for Ubereats and relatively cheap - Note: please read the house rules first before booking. 100% fast reply.
space: - Free parking on site - Netflix, Telstra Tv & Breakfast included There is a discount for early bookings.    + $20
host_about:
I would describe myself as clean, strictly tidy, professional and also a fast replier. So I’m hoping for a vice versa. 
I have 4 rooms that are for rent. The best way to book is to send me a PM( please don’t offer me cash or send me your number/ just state your reasons or intention. That will do).
To get the best value, be make sure to book in advance. It’s a lot cheaper, and I can also offer you a great deal. So for this reason, please read the house rules carefully before you book.
I also do private tours and airport pickup/drop offs ( only on weekends/or after 5pm and before 10pm) fees applied.
At my place, there are Netflix and unlimited fast Wifi, which you can help yourself with movie streaming. By day I work as a language teacher. The languages that I can speak are French, Spanish and Vietnamese. In the future, I’m hoping to learn more languages such as Korean, Italian and German. Please feel free to make a conversation with me. I would love to share my traveling stories.

name: Simple but clean and secure room in Carlton!
summary: Unknown
space: Medley Hall is a residential college of The University of Melbourne.  What this means is that during the University academic year, our rooms are occupied by students.  In the break times (Dec to mid Feb) our rooms are vacant and from $80 per night can live in one of these rooms and located perfectly and accessible by foot to all of Melbourne's favorite spots. Just around one corner is the bistro life of Carlton and The Melbourne Museum and the the University of Melbourne, and around the other are the Exhibition Gardens, the Central Business District, Chinatown, theatres and night life etc. The recent renovations and major building works at Medley Hall includes a lift to help shift between the fully renovated three levels of bedrooms (some doubles), a tv lounge room adjoined to a fully functional kitchen allowing you to cook your own food if you wish, and a modern and beautiful three story high glass atrium. The atrium ties the new with the old, a magnificent Victorian Italianate buildi
host_about: This is a residential student college.  We have 55 rooms available to be rented out to guests during the mid year break and the end of year when the students depart.  We are located a short stroll away from the city and the bustling cafe life of famous Lygon Street.  The rate of accommodation is for a single room, equipped with bedding and towel.  There are 5 showers/toilets on each floor and a kitchenette too.  It is clean, fresh and modern simple accommodation surrounded by a beautiful mansion which is heritage listed and close to everything important to visitors to Melbourne.  Happy to provide you with more information.  Just email me.

name: Great City Base 2BR + WiFi
summary: For those looking to be ideally located in Melbourne's CBD, our apartment is positioned close to many of the city's attractions and conveniences. You'll find QV Shopping Centre and State Library just across the road along with public transport, restaurants and shopping all within a few minutes walk.
space: This light filled apartment features floor to ceiling windows in both bedrooms and the living area. The apartment is fully furnished and appointed with all the essentials you need for a comfortable stay. The main bedroom includes a double bed and a streetscape view overlooking Russell Street. The second bedroom includes a single bed and a small private balcony.
host_about:
We are a young couple who call Melbourne home. We both grew up, studied and work in Melbourne. Travelling is definitely one of our loves. Between us we have spent a few years working in the UK, spent a lot of time in Asia immersing ourselves in new cultures while also learning about our Chinese heritage. We also enjoy skiing and snowboarding which has led us to beautiful Whistler and Japan. 

We consider ourselves very easy going and laid back which is why we love Melbourne life so much. Most of the time we are most happiest just spending time with friends (new and old), family, each other and of course enjoying the Melbourne food scene.

name: Modern Docklands Apartment
summary: This apartment has all the amenities including a private balcony, an ensuite bathroom, a salt water pool and fitness centre with a sauna. Harbour front dining and attractions just out the front door. Breakfast and coffee included!
space: With a beautiful view overlooking the pool and the harbour just out the front door this apartment is the best of both worlds. The CBD is only minutes away with great shopping and nightlife.
host_about: Young working professional, I love to get away and enjoy the outdoors!

name: Superb ambience is yours
summary: A beautiful two bedroom townhouse with stunning balcony awaits you. Surrounded by two golf courses and some of nature's delights. The famous Yarra Valley wineries are at your doorstep.
space: The townhouse has a beautiful upstairs living area with an open kitchen. The highlight is undoubtably the large terrace adjoining the living area. Great views of the Yarra Valley and you'll most likely see the kangaroos grazing. It is worth knowing that I do have a portable travelling cot available for anyone travelling with infants.
host_about: Hello! My name is Joe and I live in Mid Levels, Hong Kong. I look forward in meeting and hosting you soon!

name: Walk to the MCG, The Tan, Botanic gardens & train
summary: Only a moments walk to South Yarra train station, trams, Toorak rd and Chapel Street entertainment precinct.  This spacious,  one bedroom apartment is perfectly positioned to enjoy iconic Chapel streets popular boutique shopping, cafes, bars and nightlife.  While at home you can enjoy full kitchen facilities for in-house dining, a separate work-station with internet wifi and use of a heated indoor pool for some exercise.
space: Location Location Location. Perfect for business travel, shopping sprees, parks & recreation, AFL and wining & dining.  We have everything you need for a relaxing and comfortable stay. With multiple seating options and a new futon that offers and extra sleeping space if needed. In the bedroom you have a new comfy mattress with pillows to match for a nice relaxing sleep, there’s also extra blankets if needed and a TV for those who like to wind down after a long day.  The kitchen is fully equipped for those looking to eat in. In the living area there’s a small dining table with 3 chairs, a computer desk/work station and a separate sitting chair to relax. You can also access the courtyard from the living room or bedroom to catch some fresh air.  The particular apartment does not include a car space however from time to time we may have a spot available from another apartment, in any case there's usually a lot of parking available in the street. The apartment complex also has an indoor poo
host_about:
I am a professional real estate investor and property host. My goal is to help investors increase their rental yields so they can shorten their time frames with future investing and/or achieving personal goals. 

Apart from the love of real-estate, I also love to travel. When travelling I like to have a mix of hitting popular tourist attractions as well as experiencing the "live like a local" feel and really experience the culture of my chosen destination. 

Some of my favourite places  to visit are New York, Majorca, Lisbon, Positano, Greek Islands, Rome, New Zealand in a camper van and many more. I usually like to chase the sun but I also love snowboarding and like to keep active and fit. 

As a traveler I like the simplicity of self check-in so as a host I aim to automate this process as much as possible so you as the guest can simply get to your destination with no delays. 

In my travels I have found that getting some local knowledge can be very helpful so I will provide some tips and guides of things to do to get you started. 

I hope you enjoy your travels :)

summary: This is a very unique open plan studio apartment in artistic Fitzroy. It’s a beautiful space to arrive home to, and wake up in. It’s full of natural light, very well set up, and walking distance to galleries, parks, restaurants, and Melbourne city.
space: This is a beautiful apartment with a very European feeling to it. It's in the best part of Fitzroy, on Gertrude St, and it overlooks a park with big trees, which along with the abundance of natural light makes for a great atmosphere (you can hear the birds with the trams, a sound I love). It really is fantastically positioned to make the most of Melbourne.

host_about:
We call the fabulous Sandringham neighbourhood home, as does our helpful co-host Gwen.
Wanderlust has previously lured us to Europe, the Americas, Asia, Southeast Asia, the South Pacific, Africa and Outback Australia. Our interests include art, architecture, music, film, theatre and the great outdoors. When in Sandringham, we make the most of long Bayside walks on beachside tracks both summer and winter, outdoor BBQ's and swims in the clear bay water of Sandringham beach when the weather is warmer.
We enjoy the relaxed, peaceful atmosphere that Sandringham offers.  A short stroll leads to one of our many favourite cafes for coffee and breakfast, or later for dinner.  
Catching the train nearby, we may head to Brighton or Windsor for a movie, Ripponlea to `Attica' (one of the World's Top 50 restaurants), Elsternwick or Richmond for live music, or Melbourne city for a gallery or live show. For all St Kilda has to offer, including Melbourne's very own Fairy Penguin colony, the bus leaves from just minutes' away.
We would love to help with any tips about Sandringham and the city of Melbourne we love, and welcome both business and holiday travelers. 
 For more Bayside and Melbourne info, do drop by our social media page `Lostboys Apartments'.

host_about:
Hi from Bronnie and Neil ;-)
We love being airbnb hosts and sharing our homes and our beautiful city with others.
We have been airbnb hosts for over four years and during that time we have met amazing and wonderful people from all around Australia and all parts of the world.
We started with the spare room in our own home and now have 20 properties, from high end luxury to family friendly apartments that we offer our guests. We even have a 7 bedroom, 7 bathroom mansion near the sea in St Kilda for larger groups! 
We use airbnb ourselves whenever we travel and feel we know what people are looking for. Good value, great locations, clean, comfortable and friendly! All our properties are in great locations, are professionally cleaned and we use hotel quality, commercially laundered linen on comfortable beds.  We meet all our guests on arrival to say hello and are on hand to offer help, advice and inside tips of places to go and things to see. 
Most of our properties include free parking which is a real bonus in the city and Foxtel (cable) television and other homely touches so you 'can live like a local'. (You can view our properties by clicking the View Full Profile link below and clicking on the listings on the left hand side of the page). 

A little bit about ourselves ... we're pretty easy going, and love getting out and about exploring different places. We are both keen travellers and have done our fair share of it in Australia and overseas - whether backpacking, camping, or an occasional splurge on 5-star resorts! You wouldn't call us 'party animals', but we do like socialising and meeting people.  We enjoy a wide variety of interests, love the movies, eating out, popping down to the beach on our scooter or pushbikes, and enjoying the many exciting sporting events and festivals that Melbourne has to offer.
Our motto is "strangers are just friends you haven't met yet!"
Wishing you happy travels and looking forward to meeting you soon :-)

Best regards
Bronnie and Neil

space: Sweet Caroline ... at a glance * Living … Spacious 105 sqm (1,130 sq feet) ground floor single storey apartment 2 bedroom, 2 bathroom & 2 secure car spaces Private, quiet & exclusive, with no neighbouring property looking in Immaculately furnished with tasteful and comfortable furniture Great convenient location  Upmarket quiet street & area suits young and old Our cool bicycles available  Deal direct with responsive & reliable local owners * Working … Home office set-up with large vintage office table  WiFi is free with no download limit * Dining … Fully equipped kitchen Dining table extends to accommodate 6 * Entertainment … Living room: 55" LED TV + AppleTV, free Netflix + normal TV channels Master bedroom: 40" plasma TV with integrated DVD & CD player Large choice of DVD's, some board games and books * Drive or bike ride … Free 2 car spaces in secure garage (one flight of internal stairs) Bicycle provided for local use * Comfort … Private leafy balcony with dining set-up Open plan
host_about:
We love South Yarra for its charm and character, as well as the many things one can do within a short walk; there is so much choice in terms of recreation activities to parks and restaurants. And still you are so close to the city.

We have been hosting since October 2015 and thoroughly enjoy it. We constantly find ourselves brainstorming of ways to improve what we can offer; whether its that extra bit of detail in restaurant picks, to arrival tips, to fine-tuning our description so anyone new can understand why we love where we live. We also hope of course that guest see we care about ensuring their stay is as enjoyable as they can expect.

We think our style is a reflection of our own travel experiences which has been extensive and at times hectic. With that, our hosting style is one where we are non-intrusive, but always respond within minutes by phone or SMS. A solution to your needs is really only a phone or SMS away.

We actually enjoy being asked for recommendations, from the ideal travel route, to activities for kids, to restaurant and cafe choices. We only ever recommend places we know and not what we can search for. As such we are shamelessly biased to South Yarra area when it comes to cafes and restaurants! So if you are indeed interested to book with us, ask us for tips, before or even during your stay.

We'll end here by asking you to treat our home with special care! Do take note of the house rules - strictly no partying and smoking.

To keep fit and active is another big part in my life. I ride a bike to the train station and jog after work a few times in a week. I also like many other types of sports.

Hi, my name is Valeria. My husband Ben and I own and manage a number of upmarket guesthouses located in the inner Melbourne suburbs. 

We specialise in offering a new and unique opportunity to overseas, inter and intrastate visitors, career professionals, academics, post and undergraduates (3rd year and over), trainees, language students, doctors, teachers and other business specialists to gain superior inner Melbourne accommodation and lessen the stresses of moving to a new town, new state or a new country.

We offer fully furnished, centrally located properties with plenty of parking and quality fixtures and furnishings, each has an alfresco entertainment area and BBQ in a garden setting, a fully equipped property in an exclusive professional apartment house environment, where new arrivals, to Melbourne, or people going through a lifestyle transition, can experience an instant community atmosphere for medium (from two weeks), or long term stays, and say goodbye to lonely, restrictive and expensive apartment living.

No more solitary TV dinners! Each property provides apartment house accommodation on a room-by-room basis with shared kitchen, dining and lounge facilities. This style of apartment house living provides opportunities for new arrivals, to Melbourne to quickly, form friendships, build networks with other likeminded people and settle more easily into a new life. This helps to alleviate homesickness and improves their effectiveness in the workplace or place of learning.

A safe and comfortable home life makes for a happier Melbourne experience.

Typical Tenant Profiles

Flexi (Hidden by Airbnb) is open to a wide range of people from professional backgrounds usually between (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) years of age. Typical residents are overseas, inter and intrastate visitors, corporate and career professionals, academics, post and undergraduates (3rd year and over), trainees, language students, doctors, nurses, teachers and other specialists or people in the throes of re-establishing a home and life in Melbourne.

Ben and I hope you choose to stay with us and we have the opportunity to make your stay in Melbourne a life long happy memory.

At that moment, I quit my job and decided to travel in order to discover myself and the wonders that the world has to offer.

I've since become an avid traveller that has journeyed across the globe. Meeting new people, discovering new foods, embracing new cultures - it's something I'd never get sick of. 

Through these experiences, I wish to emulate the Airbnb hosts I stayed with during my own travels and give back by providing a place to stay in the beautiful city that I call Melbourne - and home. 

I'll do my utmost best to meet all my guests. And when I do, I always welcome them with my signature high-five!

It takes about 4 minutes to walk to the tram stop (trams 5 + 64) and conveniently located 8 minutes walk from Windsor train station (Sandringham line) and other trams.  There's free parking on the street.  It's a short trip to popular St Kilda Beach and Acland street restaurant strip.  Fully equipped (with character) kitchen, wooden + carpeted floors and modern bathroom.   It's a compact, light filled and relaxed apartment.
host_about:
Whilst orginally from Melbourne, I have spent quite some time living overseas (most recently Tasmania!) and am thrilled to be back in Melbourne.  I've been living here again for 5 years now and most of that time I've been an airbnb host.  I started in a lovely apartment in Elwood and now I'm in St Kilda East.  You'll see that most of my references are from my previous home in Elwood - I'm looking forward to sharing my St Kilda East home now.   I'm an old fashioned airbnb host - one that thinks that sharing my home is about cultural exchange and community.

I have an ongoing interest in the arts and currently work in arts and cultural development.  I like cycling on my faux-pony, op-shopping for hidden treasures and am so happy to be living in such a diverse and vibrant place.  

What can't I live without ............. my loved ones, being exposed to interesting adventures whilst taking time out for the quiet moments.

host_about:
Hi, 

We're a couple that lives in the gorgeous city of Melbourne, Australia. We're fortunate to have a beautiful apartment in the vibrant area of St Kilda and love the lifestyle that Melbourne offers.  We are the proud parents of Sooty the Cat and George the Schnoodle.

When we're not working, or taking George on walks, we use all the leave we have to travel the world and see as many things as we possibly can. 

Mike is an Engineer, with a love of kite-surfing, cycling and all things outdoors. 

Bec is a Marketing Manager with a love of fashion and music. 

We both love friends, good food, wine, having adventures in our Kombi and finding quirky bars around the towns we're visiting. 

We're fun, laid back and excited about meeting lots of new people on our adventures. 

We've traveled the world and had many lovely hosts in various AirBNBs.  We hope we can offer the same experience to our guests.

Bec & Mike

host_about:
~ Melbourne sky Apartments~
Dear guests:

We are Eden Charmmy and Cony. We are professional management team . 

All our apartments are unique, therefore we do not offer early check in or late check out  as my apartments are unique, we cannot just put guests in a random available room. 

My team members can speak English Korean Indonesian and Chinese . Pls feel free to contact us anytime. Thank you 
我們可以講中文 
Our working hour is from 10AM TO 10PM. 
We always answer your question within 2 hours during our business hours. 

Important information:

* We provide car park for $15 per 24 hours  ( Multi-entry) . The car park is provided by third party, you will be given an allocated car park number a day before you arrive. 

* There are few car rental companies nearby. You can search car rentals in Southern cross station to save the parking fee if you only need car for few hours.

* We are airbnb not hotel. ( Means you are staying in host's house not a hotel).
Therefore, we do not provide daily cleaning service. Additional cleaning service can be provided at extra cost. 


* Please take your personal belongings with you when you check out. We are not responsible for any lost or damage to your personal belongings.

During the warmer months you can relax outdoors on the lovely sundeck or fire-up the gas BBQ for a summer feast. Free WiFi is also available. The property has a "No Children" policy. Exclusive access to the living areas and other facilities of the cottage, including garden areas, covered carport and hard standing for additional cars. When Ed, my husband and I decided to host people to stay at our cottage, we wanted people to feel at home, for it to  be clean and comfortable. In short for people to enjoy their stay.

host_about: We are a couple in our late forties / early fifties. I am a self-employed designer-maker and sewing teacher with a penchant for handsewn and recycled textiles. My partner Rachel is an industrial designer in the area of furniture design, who is currently taking a gap year while we work on renovating our little holiday house in the Yarra Valley. Later this year we are heading to Europe for more travel adventures. We are passionate about culture and the arts, design, making things, travel, cinema, sustainability, social justice, cycling, real food, yoga and gardening amongst other things. We have been airbnb guests all over Australia and in New York and love the way that the airbnb experience makes us feel like locals in places that aren't home. We are just starting out as hosts and are looking forward to offering the local knowledge and generosity of spirit to our guests that we have found in the airbnb community. Welcome to our home!

From check-in to check-out. It is an experience not only for guests. it is for us as well. It is the whole responsibilities. 

That’s what I think, the reason which motivates me to be a host.

Melbourne is a very multi-cultural city

Me, as a host, I think is kind of connecting these different piece together, a kind of connection.
The high point of my stay was how you made me feel. And how you made me feel, it sticks. It sticks with you.”
I have the traditional way to believe.
We believe it is the relationship that provide to the guests they will enjoy,  love the place to stay.

So hospitalities if you ask me, is about care. It s about welcoming. This is about welcoming with open heart.  Welcome you to my Melbourne Apartment.

Hi, my name is Valeria. My husband Ben and I own and manage a number of upmarket guesthouses located in the inner Melbourne suburbs. 

We specialise in offering a new and unique opportunity to overseas, inter and intrastate visitors, career professionals, academics, post and undergraduates (3rd year and over), trainees, language students, doctors, teachers and other business specialists to gain superior inner Melbourne accommodation and lessen the stresses of moving to a new town, new state or a new country.

We offer fully furnished, centrally located properties with plenty of parking and quality fixtures and furnishings, each has an alfresco entertainment area and BBQ in a garden setting, a fully equipped property in an exclusive professional apartment house environment, where new arrivals, to Melbourne, or people going through a lifestyle transition, can experience an instant community atmosphere for medium (from two weeks), or long term stays, and say goodbye to lonely, restrictive and expensive apartment living.

No more solitary TV dinners! Each property provides apartment house accommodation on a room-by-room basis with shared kitchen, dining and lounge facilities. This style of apartment house living provides opportunities for new arrivals, to Melbourne to quickly, form friendships, build networks with other likeminded people and settle more easily into a new life. This helps to alleviate homesickness and improves their effectiveness in the workplace or place of learning.

A safe and comfortable home life makes for a happier Melbourne experience.

Typical Tenant Profiles

Flexi (Hidden by Airbnb) is open to a wide range of people from professional backgrounds usually between (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) years of age. Typical residents are overseas, inter and intrastate visitors, corporate and career professionals, academics, post and undergraduates (3rd year and over), trainees, language students, doctors, nurses, teachers and other specialists or people in the throes of re-establishing a home and life in Melbourne.

Ben and I hope you choose to stay with us and we have the opportunity to make your stay in Melbourne a life long happy memory.

host_about:
G'day,

I'm Joel, i'm born and raised in Sydney, which is in my opinion one of the most beautiful major cities in the world. My goal in life is to one day visit every country in the world, I hold no bias to any of them and hope that I get the opportunity. So far I have visited 42 countries. Last year I spent 1 year travelling in South and Central America and loved the opportunity I had to learn Spanish. It was a great experience and one that I will never forget. 

My hobbies include all forms of board sports, skating, surfing and snowboarding primarily. I enjoy learning about new cultures especially their foods. I grew up in an Italian restaurant so my love for food and cooking is deeply engrained in my personality. 

My style of hosting and living life in general is pretty relaxed. I will do my best to greet you at the door and make your stay as enjoyable as possible. But if you just want to chill I can totally relate. 

I also love music and watching live music. I mostly go out to see House, deep house and techno music as that scene in Sydney is easily accessible. However at home you will find me listening to hip-hop, reggae, latin, afro-beat, jazz and anything with a smooth and funky beat. 

If you need recommendations about food or music in Sydney these are probably my two strongest topics, so please don't hesitate. 

Looking forward to meeting more crazy, fun and cool people through Airbnb. 

Joel

space: Classic Granny Flat converted into a modern, cosy and nice, fully-contained, independent one bedroom apartment. Located in the quiet, leafy northern suburb of Preston in Melbourne, within 10kms of  the CBD. Tram 11 at your door step and a short trip to Brunswick St. or the city in just 20 minutes. Walking distance to the train station and easy access to freeways.    A spacious open plan living area features a practical living space and kitchen. One bedroom with large en-suite. Living room with sofa (bed) and full equipped kitchen with appliances including a Delonghi coffee machine to make your mornings easier and happier. Television, wifi (from 8 am to 11 pm) and Apple TV.  Very soon you’ll be able to enjoy an outdoor deck area to chill out and relax. host_about:
We are an Australian—Spanish family with four kids. Very happy and lively. We love to travel and spend time with the family. We love food, good wine, cooking, travel, music, carnaval, movies, books and sports.
We are serious and trustfull people. 
I’m running my own catering business and will love to share this passion with my guests, offering my home cooking as well as classes if they wish to learn how to make a “paella” or a “tortilla de patata” (Spanish omelette) among many other spanish dishes and tapas.

name: Chestnut Cottage
summary: Chestnut Hill Cottage is hidden on 6 acres of garden.  Small and self contained, with 4 rooms.  Built in 1920, in Kallista in the Dandenong Ranges, it was originally a gardener's cottage.  Central to small tourist villages and hills' walking trails.
space: 1 x Bedroom with Queen bed 1 x Living Room with fold down Queen bed from wall unit and tv with dvd player 1 x Dining Room 1 x Kitchenette (Microwave oven/2 burner induction hotplate/Bar Fridge) 1 x Bathroom/Laundry (Shower/Basin/Washing Machine/Dryer) 1 x Separate Toilet with basin Small building, but has the requirements for a comfortable short stay. A tray of breakfast items are included with your overnight stay. (Cereal, milk, bread to toast your own and a hot item eg bacon and eggs or pancakes.) Please advise if you have any dietary concerns and we will try and assist. Toaster/jug/cutlery/utensils/microwave containers/plates etc
host_about:
Hi, we live in a forest village in the Dandenong Ranges in Australia.
It is a cool temperate rainforest with walking trails and tourist villages.  We are located near puffing billy railway and the Yarra Valley.  I am a grandmother a few times over now and have a  Lodge and Cottage in our garden.  We enjoy having guests and helping them to see the local attractions.  Most guests prefer to have their own space in the self contained Cottage, but we welcome the opportunity to talk to you about our area, should you like.

I am a coffee enthusiast who can't get through the day without one. I also like punk rock in particular Green Day. I love travelling. I have been around most of Asia. However, one day I would love the chance to travel around Europe to experience its culture and history.
