We have been in Melbourne for nearly 10 years. Graduated at the University of Melbourne, we started our career in this City. We are originally from China, so we speak Chinese and embrace the Chinese culture.
We love Melbourne. People here are so nice and friendly. There are plenty of things to do in Melbourne all around the year. We have the Melbourne Cup in Spring, tennis in Summer, the Melbourne show in Autumn and skiing in Winter...and so much more. A cup of aromatic coffee in a lane or a beautiful melody on the street will remind you that this is the most liveable city in the world for a consecutive 6 years.
Come and enjoy the life in this lovely and charming city!

name: Bayside Apartment - Sea Views
summary: Female guests only.  Stunning bay views: comfortable, secure top floor, two storey, two bedroom apartment - 1 x single room - share bathroom.   Bay Street, Port Melbourne & beach at your doorstep, Melbourne CBD 3.8 kilometres via   109 tram route.
space: Tranquil and comfortable double storey apartment: close to the city, the beach and a range of restaurants, cafes and takeaway food options downstairs in Bay Street.  Apartment is on the top floor of a large complex, with bay views and within a block's walk from the beach.
host_about:
Hi, I'm a 55 year old female who lives in Port Melbourne Australia.  I work in the CBD four days a week, I'm a part-time photographer and I'm also a part-time law student.

I'm usually in and out of home, but sometimes just enjoy sitting watching tv or a film and gazing out upon the spectacular view my home has.  My home is relaxed and informal.   It is a remove your shoes at the door home though; for no other reason than to keep the pale coloured carpet clean! :-)  It's nice to pad around in bare feet on a nice clean floor.

There are many dine out options in Port Melbourne; from cheap and cheerful, to higher end.  The beach is a block away and offers great walking paths along the bay or there are hire pushbikes if you feel like riding down to St Kilda, about six kilometres away. Gasworks Market is on the the third Saturday of everyone month 10 minutes walk away, or South Melbourne market is a 30 minute walk.

Melbourne city is around 20 minutes by tram.  There are also paths into the city for cycling or walking.

There is a pool and gym available for your use, when you stay with me.

I look forward to meeting you!

Enjoy direct access to your own gym, spa, sauna, rooftop with BBQ and incredible sunset views. You've found your home in Melbourne - you'll love every moment of your time here!
space: Welcome to your home away from home. summary: Enjoy the city views from the lounge to the bedrooms of this charming, comfortable apartment. An open plan creates a cosy atmosphere for socializing. Other highlights include sleek kitchen appliances, colorful bedding, and soothing art.
space: The apartment is ideal for 2 couples to stay in or 2 adults and 2 children if they don't mind sharing a bed. It has a lift and is wheelchair friendly. There is 1  secure car park and the roof height is 2.1m. We also have a Porta cot and high Chair available for$6.00 per night .
host_about: I am a hard working person and enjoy communicating with anyone and everyone. I love being an Airbnb host as it gives me a chance to help others and provide exceptional service. I love helping people make money and I experimented on my own apartment with Airbnb. It's been empty 27 days in 4 years. I now have 16 under Airbnb. They are properties that I have bought for investors (I'm a buyers advocate) and for landlords who wanted (needed) to double their incomes.  I take a budget and I purchase all the furnishing down to the potato peeler,  accept the deliveries, set it up, wash the towels, take the photographs and then list it on Airbnb. My motto is "We do everything for you except pay for it and move in." As the short stay business has grown let me introduce Motaz Alamarat. Motaz is my colleague and was head of "front of house" at a 5 star resort in Jordan. He is the most gorgeous young man and his mind set is completely focused on ensuring all our guests have an enjoyable experience. Most of the time Motaz will meet and greet our guests any time day or night. I help out where needed. He will ensure that the apartment is clean and everything is working on your arrival. We look to ensure our landlord's property achieves a 4.8 star score.

name: Family friendly 2 Bedroom, 2 Bathroom home
summary: A single story terrace in the inner city suburb of Fitzroy, a 1 minute walk from a gym, 50 meter outdoor swimming pool, and children's playground, a 2 minute walk to surrounding cafe's, shops, excellent pubs, venues and more, our house is in is in the perfect position for anyone wanting to stay in Melbourne. A quiet street away from the bustle and noise of the busy Fitzroy nightlife - and alternatively a short walk away if the night life is what you're after.
space: The house was renovated in the 70's and has exposed brick walls and wooden panelling, with carpet throughout except for the kitchen and initial hallway entrance. The living area is open plan - with an area for dinner parties (complete with pull out table that can seat 8 ) a living area that is super comfy and very child friendly (no scary corners!)  The kitchen is small - but has all the requirements to cook anything your heart desires - gas oven, gas grill, and a 5 burner stove top. It's a small space but totally functional.  Our favourite feature is the very large lightwell that we have converted into an indoor garden - This lets sun into these otherwise traditionally very dark terraces and looks beautiful. We have recently installed an antique claw foot bathtub complete with sky views and steaming hot water.  Possums can be heard every now and then running along the roof - and regularly hang about in the back garden.  Photo's of the the back garden and study will be posted shortly -
host_about:
I am a 33 year old theatre director, living in Melbourne, Australia. 

I grew up in Melbourne, and moved to Sydney in 2008 to study at the National Institute of Dramatic Art (NIDA) and lived there with my now husband, until 2014. We lived all over, Randwick, North Bondi, Newtown, Chatswood - and fell in love with Sydney and all it has to offer.  

I direct theatre and opera shows and have worked with lots of companies across the country, Sydney Theatre Company, Melbourne Theatre Company, The Malthouse, State Theatre of South Australia, Sydney Chamber Opera and Victorian Opera to name a few. 

I adore my job, and love collaborating with other theatre makers.  The odd hours, the fact that no two days are the same, and that I get to work with extraordinary people make me very grateful to work in the industry.  

I'm married with two kids, currently sporting a 4 month old baby and 3 year old girl.  We live in Fitzroy in Melbourne, in a charming single story terrace. I love tinkering around the house, cooking, flowers, and gardening. (mind you I don't get much time for this given my new status as mother of two!) 

Fav things include watching cartoons, going to art galleries (installation art a fav)  drinking good coffee, going for walks through gardens, swimming at every opportunity, reading good books, having dinner parties and talking till all hours of the morning (though since kids that's become kind of a challenge.) I love hanging out with my family and laughing and mucking about cracking jokes.  I love my friends and giggling with them.  

I love laughing, jokes, comedy, and think life is far too important to be taken seriously. I'm incredibly grateful to be healthy and have a healthy little family.

name: Creative, Cozy, Designer Apartment
summary: A light filled spacious room, in a stylish designer warehouse. Located in the centre of the culturally rich & creative Brunswick. Close to public transport, surrounded by eclectic food & quality cafes. Experience Melbourne with all it's highlights. Brunswick is a great place to get totally submersed in. Plus it is also a really great place to stay while catching the convenient public transport in and around the CBD.
space: Modern designer conversion within a stunning historically listed warehouse. This eclectic and visually stimulating space is home and studio for two Freelance Artists.  You will be on the doorstop of all the action that Brunswick has to offer, from diverse myriad of cultural cuisine, the funkiest cafe's in Melbourne, street-art on every corner, galleries, shopping and general exploration of one of Melbourne's most diverse suburbs. Once your done with Brunswick, your only moments away to multiple modes of public transport (tram, train, bus), with a short 15 min trip into the CBD.
host_about:
Hello. My name is Amos. I am a visual artist, with painting being my main practice. I really enjoy my job and love being creative and finding ways to get my artwork exposed.

I have been hosting for over 3 years now, and really like meeting new people and hearing their stories.

If you come to say at our wonderful place here in Brunswick, you will be staying with me and my lovely partner Kat. We both work from home part time, so we have our studios set up in the house.

name: Designer/makers dwelling above print studio shop
summary: This is a Melbourne artist/designer/makers home, which is a large dwelling above active studio shop space. Collingwood is a historically significant area and the building features high ceilings and pressed tin, and was probably built in the 1870s. Collingwood is the best place to be in Melbourne in my opinion, plenty of amazing places to eat and drink, lots of great venues with gigs - never boring! The room I have for guests is cosy, but quiet and and private.
space: This place is the dwelling area on top of a studio shop in a historic heritage listed building. The shop is the front of a design studio where we screen print a range of beautiful locally made clothing.   As well as a screen printing studio, we have a band rehearsal and recording space (not for guest use). Guests are welcome to check out the printing process and learn a bit about screen printing, if they are interested. The shop is open most days and we offer a 15% discount for all guests !
host_about:
I run an independent design label called Captain Robbo. We specialise in print for textiles and have our own line based in Collingwood Melbourne. 
I love to travel and explore new cities for downtime.

(ADSL 2+, 200 gig per month) All linen and towels are supplied as well as cooking equipment and utensils. A Range of teas and co
host_about:
Hi There,

I'm Jonathan, I'm in my mid 40's, sometimes older sometimes younger and I love to travel. 

In terms of a home I love a comfy couch, I love a deep bath and I love full blockout curtains. 

5 things I can't live without?

Books, I love a good book.
Good food. I love sharing a great meal with others.
Long sleep in's on Sundays or any day really.
Water. I love swimming in the ocean or rivers. Lets keep them clean.
Music. Anything from opera to house.

As your host, I will be on call to make your stay as comfortable as possible. If anything goes wrong during your stay, say the washing machine won't start or something, I will have it sorted immediately. I've had guest stay at my place for 3 month and then extend up to 16 months. I've had guests who moved out and then told me if they could stay forever they would be very happy. 

As someone who has travelled a lot with work and stayed in hotels motels and apartments both long and short term, I set out to create a space that was a real home away from home. Somewhere where you can feel safe, warm and cosy and enjoy a good home cooked meal. It was all about atmosphere. A deep bath to relax in, comfy couches to put your feet up on, a big TV to tune out to and stunning view whilst enjoying your breakfast. In winter turn on the gas log fireplace and enjoy a glass of wine. Head out to one of the many great eating establishments on Chapel St, Fitzroy St or take a tram to the city. the tram stop is a 2 minute walk away.

Everyone who has stayed at Charnwood has enjoyed their stay. I'm sure you will too. Great location, affordably priced and in a very convenient but quiet street.

host_about:
Hi there.  I'm originally from New Zealand but moved to Melbourne 19 years ago. 
Like most people who arrive in this wonderful city we think we are going to move on, but as soon as we get here ... well, there are reasons no-one ever wants to leave!  I was lucky enough to find this great house in the best part of Fitzroy so here I still am.   I have a habit of collecting things hence all the vintage love around the house.  Over the last decade+ I've shared my home with hundreds people from all around the world.  Things I can't live without?  Friends, freedom, Fitzroy...  If you think my home sounds like your kind of pad I'd love to hear from you and know what brings you to Melbourne.

host_about: I've been a host for the better part of 2017 and achieved super host after 3 months. I really enjoy the process of hosting and providing the means for a great stay.  As a young family we lived at the Collingwood location for about 5 years so we know the area well and have many recommendations to share. I grew up on the south side of Melbourne but quickly became an Inner-North convert 10 years ago. Food, music, live acts, comedy, shopping, it's much more creative and fashionable here on this side of the Yarra.  When travelling with my family we've actually only used AirBnB a few times but looking forward to more experiences. The concept of 'trust' is what I like most about AirBnB which appeals to my optimistic nature.

space: Unknown
host_about:
Hi my name is Dawei, I started doing Airbnb September 2015. 

I'm a 20 years old undergraduate student currently studying commercial law. I like to watch movies and play video games. Sometimes I could spend my whole day in my room just play games. I thought that there isn't much things to do outside and I thought the World was a boring place. When I'm not playing games, I would read news on the internet just to catch up with the rest of the world. That's how I knew Airbnb. 

One day, my father come to me, talked about doing short term renting. He has got few new apartments that our relatives bought which needs to be rented out. I told him about Airbnb and he thought we could really make it work. So I asked my best friend if he is interested to be my partner for this, and he said yes. We started almost immediately, planning, buying furnitures to started taking guests in just two weeks. 

Then it really changed me.

I met with travellers around the world. Every body was so polite and friendly.  When I talk to them I can feel the excitement and happiness. It's totally  different compare to what I thought people are like. Maybe because this communicate is great, I don't know.  Then I  thought "I want to be people like my guests". I want people around me to feel life is great and there are a lot to look forward to. The guests really gave me a lot motivation towards my work and my life. Here I have to thank you all.

After one month, the revenue was great, however take away the interests and loans, all kinds of fees and salary for my partner, there are really not much left for me. But I think that's enough, I'm still a student, I have to spend time on study and don't have much things to spend money on anyway, being able to save money for a holiday with my girl friend every few month is perfect for me. 

After all these experience, I felt it really changed my life and how I view the world. Doesn't matter if I fail or succeed it's  going to effect the rest of my life in a very positive way, that's something really valuable to me.

space: We recently purchased this beautiful home (hence the real estate agency photographs in use!) and have just moved in. The house is the perfect blend of Art Deco restoration and modern extension. host_about:
About Peter and Marianne

Hi there, we have lived in Melbourne most of our lives. We have raised a family, are running our own businesses and love to travel when we can.  We hope to facilitate a wonderful experience for people staying in our property, just as others have done for us when we have been overseas. We always aim to meet our guests on arrival and to relate to people in a respectful and friendly way.

Our travel experiences in the last 10 years have included all states in Australia, Europe, UK, South Africa, Canada and Alaska. Many years ago before having a family we also travelled around China and South East Asia and would love to revisit these regions. In our travels we have been most captivated by fabulous scenery and by the amazing people we have met, whether it be fellow travellers or lovely locals who we have connected with. 

Peter has been an electrician for more than 40 years and has a great passion for Australian Rules football and playing golf with good friends. Marianne is a psychologist and loves to read, catch up with friends over a coffee and take our dogs for long walks. Occasionally our daughter Jess will help you check in, she is working on a PhD and likes to take her eyes off a computer screen and help out when she can.

Melbourne is a wonderful city to visit, as it offers so much in cultural, sporting and dining experiences to discover. We’d be happy offer suggestions to help you to explore your interests while in Melbourne.

We have been hosts on Airbnb for a couple of years and have hosted friends and family for many more years, providing a warm, welcoming and relaxing experience. We welcome your inquiries about staying in Melbourne.

We look forward to meeting you.

Peter and Marianne
(& sometimes Jess)

host_about:
I'm Linton, I own and run a short-stay management company, Beyond a Room, here in Melbourne. If you book with me you'll be communicating with both myself and my staff.

I’m an entrepreneur, architecture graduate, photographer, cyclist (NOT the lycra kind), volunteer, adventurer and problem solver.

During my studies I worked at various cafes and architecture offices to save up for shoestring trips around the world. My grandma once told me I had ‘champagne taste but a beer budget’ and it’s a motto I’ve enjoyed applying to different parts of my life to get the more out of less and find enjoyment in the little things.

I love discovering authentic experiences when I travel and I love being able to share the opportunity with others, to live like a local when they travel too.

Some of my most memorable trips have been couch-surfin across Russia while taking the Trans Siberian, living in Helsinki and learning to hand build furniture, riding a vintage steel bicycle through France to race in L’Eroica and buying a car on craigzlist in Los Angeles and driving across the south, east and north coasts to arrive in Vancouver.

My listings are all managed by Beyond a Room and are all given names that I think reflect the character of the property and area. My aim is to give guests a unique and local perspective on the location and share my knowledge and experience of this wonderful city with travellers so that they feel at home. Search Beyond a Room to find out more about how we can help manage your airbnb.

I try to keep all my calendars up to date so if it’s available in the calendar, you can usually just go ahead and book

name: Cosy pad by the Yarra in Northcote
summary: Cosy apartment in a tranquil setting available for long term stays only.  I will be away between the 13th and 26th of December (two weeks), and I am looking for a single person (female preferred) or a peace loving mature couple to take over my apartment for that period.  My tranquil one bedroom apartment is close to public transport, the Yarra River and cafes and music venues in Melbourne's music capital Northcote. It promises a blend of culture and nature.
space: It is located on the first floor and gets ample sunlight during the day. Plants inside and outside the apartment (on the balcony) add a green touch, making it a very relaxed place for reading, writing and yoga. It is ideal for one person wanting to finish writing that book, or for a couple seeking a cosy and relaxed time.
host_about: I love the wilderness and I also love the warmth of human communities. I now live in Melbourne, call Australia home, but India made me and that is how I will always identify. Reading, writing, good conversations and food shared with wonderful friends I make while travelling keep me alive and happy.

host_about:
LittleStay is a boutique short stay company specialising in homemade hospitality. We are passionate about traveling, exploring, and sharing. Bitten by the travel bug when we were young, we love to jump on a plane and explore the world. Spending our days and nights away from home with new friends, exchanging our experiences, and building new unforgettable memories. LittleStay is here to help create those memories. 

That's the idyllic part, but in our real life we all have bills, mortgages and obligations that we wish we could leave at home and don't have to travel with.

Consequentially LittleStay was born to help with that dream, a company that allow people like us and others to travel, live, experience or start a new life without the everyday struggle of life back “home”.

LittleStay wants you to feel comfortable entrusting us with your largest asset. We will consider your home our home while we manage it. It is our reputation on the line if something is amiss. We do not take that lightly.  LittleStay wants you to be a part of our LittleFamily. We value your partnership and thusly, if you are holidaying and want to stay at one of our properties, you’ll receive insider rates. You can even reserve your own property for your family and friends that are visiting. 

We take care of virtually everything. Our level of cleaning is second to none. Our customer service is beyond compare. Our commitment to you, the owner, our guest, our community is unquestionable. 

We believe a happy home is a filled home so if you have a property that is not happy, please contact us to see how we can help you. 

Or if you're one of our amazing guests helping us, please let us know how we can make your stay more enjoyable. 

Warmest Regards
The LittleStay Team

name: Uninterrupted views
summary: My place is in the centre of Melbourne, directly above the current GPO (General Post Office).  The building is connected to the Emporium Shopping Centre, Melbourne Central (shops and underground railway station) and Myers and David Jones. My place is good for business travellers, because I'm also working and tend to work after hours.  Singles and couples on short holidays are also welcome. You’ll enjoy uninterrupted views of the city to the east.
space: Lovely apartment
host_about: I'm an Australian scientist and professional engineer (civil, environmental, working mostly with water, especially groundwater). I lived in Sydney until the end of my first degree.  Since then I've lived in Cooma in southern NSW, Pasadena and Boston (USA) for 6+ years, and Perth WA for more than 30 years. I've travelled widely, and I've worked in many countries (New Guinea, Egypt, Thailand, France, Vietnam, New Caledonia, Peru, Colombia and more). I've worked on faculty at UWA, as a research scientist with CSIRO, as a consultant, and as founder of several IT-related startups.  I recently moved to Melbourne to start again. Hoping to reconnect with music (I used to sing - everything from choral music to jazz and opera), dance and theatre. English is my first language, but I speak French, some German, some Spanish and I've started learning Mandarin.

Six things we can't live without:- 
1. Each other.
2. Family & friends.
3. Morning coffee and a long, hot shower. 
4. Long Sunday walks. 
5. A dinner table full of laughter. 
6. A camera to capture the moment. 

Our favourite six spots in Melbourne. 
1. The walk from StKilda to Port Melbourne beach. 
2. Seawinds on the Mornington Peninsula. 
3. The laneways of Melbourne.  
4. Ripponlea Estate. 
5. Yarra River walk. 
6. The Royal Botanical Gardens. 

We like to think that we have created a home away from home in the apartment we host on airbnb.

The apartments are situated in the lively and dynamic suburbs of South Yarra and East Melbourne/CBD. 

All of our apartments are within 200metres of a tram AND train stop and in close proximity to other public transport, a range of major shopping precincts and multiple dining and entertainment choices in the pulsating heart of Melbourne’s cosmopolitan districts.

Apartment Stays Melbourne provides a number of different furnished apartment configurations to suit all needs and are therefore ideally suited for the business traveller, academics, students, doctors, teachers, other professionals, long term travellers and families.

name: The Stables, Island of Richmond
summary: Superbly located hotel style accommodation in a quiet courtyard with independent access.
space: The Stables is a single bedroom unit, akin to a hotel room, which is  separated from the main residence by the yard.     Built in 1900, The Stables were lovingly and sympathetically renovated in 2010.  They retain their original red brick floors and timber doors, but now feature a beautiful modern ensuite.    Location is everything, and you would be hard pressed to get closer to the MCG.  All of the attractions of the city are just a pleasant stroll through the beautiful parkland.  This is an excellent location if you are going to concerts or sporting events at Rod Laver Arena or AAMI Stadium.   Located centrally between Bridge Rd and Swan St, which are home to fantastic cafes, restaurants, and shopping. Trams, trains, and buses are all nearby. summary: This privately owned retro 1 bedroom apartment will make you feel like you’re living in the 50’s with all the modern conveniences of today. Live in Melbourne.
space: Living Space The lounge is a fun blast from the past. With the huge art deco windows that lets the morning sun cascade onto the midcentury inspired furniture. You’ll find yourself right at home lounging on the bright orange chaise watching Netflix or relaxing on the Hans Wegner Shell chair with a book.  But we suggest turning the Shell Chair around and taking in the amazing view of one of Melbourne’s oldest buildings, Town Hall. Sleeping Space The bedroom is a cozy space that has room to move around. The bed has a mixture of colours and textures to make your nights rest more enjoyable. You will fall right to sleep with the luxurious bamboo cotton sheets and washed linen duvet. Don’t worry, you’ll be able to wake up to that gorgeous view from the bedroom as well. All you will need to do is bring your food to cook up a great meal… Or pop in last nights meal i
host_about:
LittleStay is a boutique short stay company specialising in homemade hospitality. We are passionate about traveling, exploring, and sharing. Bitten by the travel bug when we were young, we love to jump on a plane and explore the world. Spending our days and nights away from home with new friends, exchanging our experiences, and building new unforgettable memories. LittleStay is here to help create those memories. 

That's the idyllic part, but in our real life we all have bills, mortgages and obligations that we wish we could leave at home and don't have to travel with.

Consequentially LittleStay was born to help with that dream, a company that allow people like us and others to travel, live, experience or start a new life without the everyday struggle of life back “home”.

LittleStay wants you to feel comfortable entrusting us with your largest asset. We will consider your home our home while we manage it. It is our reputation on the line if something is amiss. We do not take that lightly.  LittleStay wants you to be a part of our LittleFamily. We value your partnership and thusly, if you are holidaying and want to stay at one of our properties, you’ll receive insider rates. You can even reserve your own property for your family and friends that are visiting. 

We take care of virtually everything. Our level of cleaning is second to none. Our customer service is beyond compare. Our commitment to you, the owner, our guest, our community is unquestionable. 

We believe a happy home is a filled home so if you have a property that is not happy, please contact us to see how we can help you. 

Or if you're one of our amazing guests helping us, please let us know how we can make your stay more enjoyable. 

Warmest Regards
The LittleStay Team

I'm New Zealander living and working in Melbourne. I recently bought a new apartment in the fantastic Ripponlea Village, just 7.5 kms from the CBD or a quick 15 min train trip (the train station is within 300 mtrs). 

Over the past 5 years, I was house & pet-sitting full time so I'm loving having my own space again. People often ask me to come back and look after their pets when they travel, so I plan to do housesits throughout the year.  Therefore, I'm listing my apartment on Airbnb for help with the mortgage while I'm away.  You can find out more about me by running a web search for: "kirsten house proud trusted sitter"

I have made my apartment very welcoming for local or international visitors, holidaymakers or business professionals. I'm a huge fan of Melbourne and can also offer great advice on places to see/eat or things to do during your visit. I hope you enjoy your stay and look forward to welcoming you on your arrival!

space: Inspired by Nordic interior design throughout, the first and second bedroom contains beautifully styled queen beds while the third bedroom comprises of two single beds, all of which have fresh and luxurious linen to keep you comfortable during your stay. Upon arrival, you will also find the bathroom stocked with body wash, hand soap, shampoo, conditioner, toilet paper and fresh bath towels. The living room features a 6-seater dining table, flat screen TV, coffee table, cosy sofa bed (that folds backwards into a bed for one) and a fully equipped kitchen perfect for cooking up a delicious meal. Separate from the living room is an outdoor area with outdoor seating ideal for lounging throughout the day.
host_about:
Roomerang is an end-to-end short stays team based in Melbourne.

We are avid travellers and know how hard it can be to find comfortable and cosy, yet affordable accommodation. We try to remove all the complications surrounding your stay, so you can focus on other important aspects of your trip. And if you feel we have left anything out, let us know and we would love to help.

Roomerang provides professionally cleaned and well-kept, affordable stays presenting you with a home to return to no matter who you are, where you're from or what you are here for!

name: Romantic Tiny House Garden Getaway Brunswick Edge
summary: A rustic chic, boho luxe getaway in inner Melbourne with the option to book spa packages onsite. Just over the brunswick border near multiple public transport options to take you to city Brunswick, Brunswick East and  Calton in one easy step. This romantic  little getaway is separated from  beautiful Victorian brick house being run a beauty therapy salon and medi spa ... ask about our romance packages to book in for a massage or facial or both ... we also have a couples treatment room available ... and relaxing luxurious baths can be accommodated in the spas bathroom after work hours ... an urban get away close to some of the best food and night life in Melbourne. You have your own private out door area to use with a barbecue and outdoor fire to cosy up around
space: A tiny eco garden house with quality furnishings ... feather doonas, 500tc sheets, velvet curtains and quirky details. Your own outdoor area with seating and a barbecue and option to book romantic spa packages. Breakfast and tea coffee etc is provided and all free range and mostly organic with lactose and gluten free options catered to aswell. Its cosy for winter with a warm heater and electric blankets and fire pits for outdoors. A quiet romantic getaway where you feel like you've left the city whlist having it all on your doorstep. We are all inclusive, love is love, I dont care about the colour of your skin, your faith or who you love, so long as you are good people and dont hate on cats lol
host_about: I'm a kiwi girl who moved to Melbourne around 4 years ago. I love all the arts, architecture, food, parks and beaches and events this vibrant city has to offer.. and that where I live I hear Italian, Greek and Lebanese most days, it's like a little bit of Europe and oo did I mention the food ? I like things a bit quirky and wherever I travel I prefer to check out local coffee shops and people watch and troll through the streets and flea markets looking for finds for my house and me... there may be a ridiculous number of vintage dresses in my wardrobe.Beautiful spaces make me happy, I like air BnB because generic hotels bore me senseless. I run my own organic beauty therapy business and I try to live my life as ethically as possible... I am a clean and bubbly person and will happily look after and love any pets that come with places.. I have a beautiful Bengal cat called Benny, he has the most gorgeous big blue eyes. Life is too short to not make the most of every moment so I try find beauty in the small things ... I just wish there was more time to travel! I speak basic French and German.

Paul, Complete Host

Hi, we are Maki and Roy Airbnb - Tarneit.

During your stay Maki will be your primary contact.

We are both ‘professional’ people, involved largely in Information Technology and other enterprises. We are not at all geeky, easy to talk to and speaks few languages.

We love Melbourne’s vibrancy and its cosmopolitan culture and consider it to be the best city in Australia. However, don't take my word for it; The Economist annual study (Aug 2017). named Melbourne as the "world's most livable city", for the 7th year running.

Melbourne offers an outstanding variety of food and wines to suit all tastes and budgets, world-class places to visit, and it host major events. 

We love wining & dining, health & wellness activites, photography, travelling, exploring new places and experiencing different cultures.

We are also a one-stop shop providing an affordable Maki and Roy Airbnb Tarneit Melbourne accommodation, airport transfer (pick up/drop off), Melbourne Prestige Tours (private tour) outside Melbourne CBD, and wedding package. We had overseas couple use all our services from airport transfer, Maki and Roy Airbnb accommodation, wedding celebrant and ceremony package and finishing it off with our  personalized private tour package (Melbourne Prestige Tour) as part of their honeymoon.

We love referrals! Please kindly share with all your friends and family about our one-stop shop services.

summary: Villiage Belle 5 star Hotel is here! Sleek, contemporary, double-storey venue encompassing all-year-round beer garden, public bar and cocktail lounge across four distinct areas:The Garden Bar, Balcony Bar, Public Bar and The Doulton Lounge. The "Belle" of St Kilda. The perfect base for exploring Melbourne,  St Kilda’s beautiful beach a moments walk, vibrant bars and restaurants are on your doorstep and the rest of Melbourne is only a short tram ride away.
space: Village Belle Hotel is an iconic building with an excellent reputation that has been around since 1891 and is ready to unveil its new modern look after a recent refurbishment. Sip on cocktails in the year round beer garden or enjoy a bistro -style meal while taking in the great views down Acland Street. Want to celebrate?  From dinner, cocktails, live music, weekday lunch specials and DJs to chilling in the Doulton Lounge booths, this is one day and night destination that defies temperamental weather all-year-round but never the fun. If you want to continue the party after making the most of Melbourne’s amazing nightlife or enjoy some peace and quiet after a long day of sight seeing there’s no need to worry about the noise as the apartment has been built with specially designed soundproof walls. It's a short stroll to two train stations (5/10min) and it's approx a 20/25min journey from the front door to Flinders and Southern Cross stations. Seddon's our favourite inner-western suburb, sandwiched between the ultra-trendy Yarraville and the cultural hub of Footscray.
space: Our apartment is unique because for a one bedroom apartment it's big, and thanks to the layout and wealth of natural light, it feels even bigger. Our space is clean, modern, well furnished and we're sure you will love it.
host_about:
I live in Melbourne and love my city but also really enjoy travelling. My girlfriend and I are often away and we want to share our spacious one bedroom 'penthouse' with you while we are. If you're letting us into your home you can be sure that we will look after it like our own.

Our favourite things to do while travelling are walk, eat the most delicious food we can find and regularly stop for a drink or two.

name: Faraday Cottage Carlton Experience - inner city
summary: Melbourne is a diverse, multi-cultural city with the best food & coffee in the world (if we do say so ourselves). Experience life like a local at Faraday Cottage, all nationalities & cultures welcome. Faraday Cottage is a cosy Edwardian home in an excellent location, just a stone's throw away from the Carlton Gardens and Melbourne Museum and 2.3km from the CBD. Lygon St (Carlton), Brunswick St, Gertrude St (Fitzroy) & Smith St (Collingwood) are all within walking distance.
space: 5-STAR MATTRESSES Having stayed at hundreds of hotels and Airbnbs it never ceases to amaze us how many provide poor mattresses and bedding. At Faraday Cottage you'll sleep on excellent top of the line mattresses more fit for a presidential suite than an Airbnb. You'll feel how comfortable the mattresses are as soon as you lie down and let the fatigue of the day melt away. Each mattress has a plush pillow top giving a luxurious comfort without the mattress feeling too hard or too soft. The 3-zone pocket spring system means you won't feel your partner tossing and turning all night and the double box walls mean you can sleep right up to the edge of the mattress without it caving in or losing comfort. 5-STAR LINEN AND TOWELS We provide 5-star hotel quality fresh linen and towels. Each guest is given a bath towel and face washer and the beds are made with two fresh sheets and a fresh cover on the quilt. Extra blankets and quilts are provided so you'll be warm and toasty at night. 5-STAR SOF
host_about:
My fiancé and I met traveling in Buenos Aires, fell in love and spent two and a half out of the next three years traveling and living together overseas.

I'm Australian, born in Sydney, raised in Tasmania and I've called Melbourne home for the past 10 years.

My fiancé is Brazilian, born and raised in Curitiba until she was 15 before moving to Fortaleza with her family.

We love experiencing new cultures, meeting new people, trying new foods and learning more about ourselves and the world around us.

On our travels, we've stayed in hostels, hotels, Airbnb, friends houses, couches and everything in between. We have a good idea of what makes a place comfortable and enjoyable for a traveler, including for business, and we aim to bring that comfort and enjoyment to our own listings on Airbnb.

I make sure that I stay up to date with whats going on in Melbourne on the culinary front and am happy to share it with you if you are interested. (I keep the City guide as updated as possible)

name: Luxurious Self Contained Pool House
summary: Our luxurious and private Pool House is tucked away in an English style garden with a swimming pool and spa. We are located in a secure and safe suburb,  close to the city centre which is easily accessible by car, train, tram or even by bicycle.
space: Enjoy a tranquil stay in a magnificent garden with pool and spa, in a quiet suburb conveniently located close to the city centre. We accept a maximum of two guests only. Location Kooyong is a tiny sought-after suburb wedged between Malvern, Hawthorn, and Toorak--one of Melbourne's most exclusive suburbs. We are only 7km from the city centre. Our home backs on to Kooyong Park and there is easy access to the city which is only 10 minutes by train, or 25 minutes by bicycle path all the way (complimentary bikes available).  Amenities The modern Pool House is fully air conditioned and heated, and has its own private, separate entry. It is fitted with a smoke alarm and gas detector, and even has its own security system. There is unlimited broadband wireless Internet in the Pool House. We also provide a wireless printer (Mac or PC) to print out plane tickets or correspondence. The bathroom features a frame-less shower and there is a fully kitted out kitchenette with a two hob Miele gas stove,
host_about:
We are privileged to live in a lovely part of Melbourne. We have one teenager left at home, and one small friendly dog that lives mostly inside.

I am self employed and work mostly from home, which is ideal for having guests come and stay.

I love walking, cycling, cooking, reading, theatre, live music and travel and I try to keep up-to-date with what is happening in and around Melbourne, so I am able to recommend restaurants, activities and festivals. I am particularly fond of quirky events around town and am always dragging someone along!

When we travel we forgo the homogeneous chain hotels and stay in anything from camper vans to B&Bs to boutique hotels--accommodation that reflects a bit of the culture around us. I particularly love destinations that offer an insight into a completely different way of life.

I look forward to welcoming you to our part of the world and giving you some great tips on Melbourne.

space: Carefully curated, spacious, striking and sophisticated; The Birdcage boasts more than an enviable Melbourne location. Earthy tones, dark cabinetry and bespoke art set a relaxing mood in the open plan living, dining and kitchen. And while your eye is drawn to the cityscape beyond the exterior paneling, the sophisticated living room and kitchen commands attention.  Conversation flows seamlessly from meal preparation in the state of the art contemporary kitchen, that features striking dark cabinetry and stylish bench seating with a view, to the dining table which comfortably seats up to eight guests. While in the living room the lighter colour palette, fire place and combination of textures add warmth to create a cosy zone. Why stay in a hotel when you can enjoy the space and amenity of a designer home?

Luxico manages designer and luxury homes across Melbourne, Sydney, Palm Beach, Byron Bay, Noosa and the Mornington Peninsula with many new locations coming in 2018.

All Luxico homes are  fully equipped with 5-star linens, towels, luxury toiletries, gourmet welcome hampers, free Wi-Fi and all the essential items that you will require during your stay.

Luxico's Housekeeping and Concierge Services teams are on hand to assist with airport transfers, grocery deliveries, catering, extra cleaning and anything else you might require.

Guests travelling with children can request toys, activities, travel cots and high chairs, whilst pet owners have a number of great properties to choose from with doggy beds, water bowls and other items provided to minimize your luggage.

host_about:
Hi from Bronnie and Neil ;-)
We love being airbnb hosts and sharing our homes and our beautiful city with others.
We have been airbnb hosts for over four years and during that time we have met amazing and wonderful people from all around Australia and all parts of the world.
We started with the spare room in our own home and now have 20 properties, from high end luxury to family friendly apartments that we offer our guests. We even have a 7 bedroom, 7 bathroom mansion near the sea in St Kilda for larger groups! 
We use airbnb ourselves whenever we travel and feel we know what people are looking for. Good value, great locations, clean, comfortable and friendly! All our properties are in great locations, are professionally cleaned and we use hotel quality, commercially laundered linen on comfortable beds.  We meet all our guests on arrival to say hello and are on hand to offer help, advice and inside tips of places to go and things to see. 
Most of our properties include free parking which is a real bonus in the city and Foxtel (cable) television and other homely touches so you 'can live like a local'. (You can view our properties by clicking the View Full Profile link below and clicking on the listings on the left hand side of the page). 

A little bit about ourselves ... we're pretty easy going, and love getting out and about exploring different places. We are both keen travellers and have done our fair share of it in Australia and overseas - whether backpacking, camping, or an occasional splurge on 5-star resorts! You wouldn't call us 'party animals', but we do like socialising and meeting people.  We enjoy a wide variety of interests, love the movies, eating out, popping down to the beach on our scooter or pushbikes, and enjoying the many exciting sporting events and festivals that Melbourne has to offer.
Our motto is "strangers are just friends you haven't met yet!"
Wishing you happy travels and looking forward to meeting you soon :-)

Best regards
Bronnie and Neil

summary: Coming to Melbourne for footy or tennis? This apartment is only 20 minutes walk to MCG and Rod Laver Arena. Or here for relaxation or on business, this spacious light-filled aptm & heritage-listed building is located on the Paris end of the city & iconic Hosier Lane and near to major business offices. We are right behind Gucci and diagonally across from Chanel and Grand Hyatt hotel. Superb location With 110sqm living space & 3m high ceiling it is larger than most normal 2BR aptm.
space: Perched above the city, this apartment on the seventh floor opens into a large sunny living and dining space with three meter high ceilings and panoramic views windows over the city. Add to this are two spacious, beautifully furnished bedrooms with queen sized beds which make it perfect for two friends travelling together, two couples or a family, marbled finished bathrooms and well designed kitchen with granite bench tops. Each room has built-in wardrobes with hangers to provide plenty of storage for you to unpack and make yourself feel at home, as well as reading materials and a study desk for you to put your laptop and electronics.  The kitchen has a microwave, electric stove top and oven plus all the diningware and cooking utensils you need to whip up a meal with ingredients you can get at the groceries 100 metres from the building. There is also a dishwasher and detergent is provided for your convenience. Quality bed linens and towels are all provided for and bathrooms are fully e
host_about:
Tom and I are young professionals who work and live in Melbourne as we love our city. We love to travel and have stayed at several AirBnBs ourselves which is what made us decide to list our apartment out to fellow travellers. Always happy to give suggestions and tips on what to do and see in Melbourne - there's always something on and we'd love to help you maximise your stay here.

Our recent trips include:
- Philippines – I worked about a year here on a very remote island 15 hours from Manila by ferry. The people were amazing and so was the country. Great place for diving!
- Malaysia – we indulged in so much street food.
- Singapore – more food!
- Japan – visited manga museums, awe-inspired by amazingly advanced technology, ate lots of raman ordered from vending machines
- France – I did a summer abroad in Angouleme in high school then in Vichy so try to go back whenever we get the chance!
- New York - so much to see & do. We love the art scene and indulging on street food.

We are always planning our next trip and hope to one day visit Norway and road trip through the US up to Canada to see friends in Vancouver then go up to the Rockies.

Hello ! My name is Sarah May. I have hosted in AirBnb many times,  and have used it a few in my random travels. So far it has given me some unforgettable and memorable experiences. I am currently an exchange student in Beijing. 

Interests include discussing and laughing into the evening, while sharing a bottle of wine. Picnicking in the park. Going for long walks at night in the summer. And of course, studying language.

As for being a guest, I am considerate of others' time and personal space. Of course, I would also love to get to know you if the opportunity is available.

大家好,我叫管梅梅｡我在墨尔本当过主人很多次,旅途中当宾人几次｡通过这个平台,我积累了不少难忘记的经验,非常赞成这样的模式｡我目前在北京学习汉语｡

我的爱好:到晚上一直发笑并谈论无数的话题,分享一瓶红酒｡公园里做野餐｡夏天晚上散步｡最后的,最重要的,学习各种各样的语言｡

就宾人而言,我尊重您的时间和自己的生活,也不吵｡当然,如果有机会的话,我非常愿意认识您｡

谢谢!

host_about:
Hi, my name is Valeria. My husband Ben and I own and manage a number of upmarket guesthouses located in the inner Melbourne suburbs. 

We specialise in offering a new and unique opportunity to overseas, inter and intrastate visitors, career professionals, academics, post and undergraduates (3rd year and over), trainees, language students, doctors, teachers and other business specialists to gain superior inner Melbourne accommodation and lessen the stresses of moving to a new town, new state or a new country.

We offer fully furnished, centrally located properties with plenty of parking and quality fixtures and furnishings, each has an alfresco entertainment area and BBQ in a garden setting, a fully equipped property in an exclusive professional apartment house environment, where new arrivals, to Melbourne, or people going through a lifestyle transition, can experience an instant community atmosphere for medium (from two weeks), or long term stays, and say goodbye to lonely, restrictive and expensive apartment living.

No more solitary TV dinners! Each property provides apartment house accommodation on a room-by-room basis with shared kitchen, dining and lounge facilities. This style of apartment house living provides opportunities for new arrivals, to Melbourne to quickly, form friendships, build networks with other likeminded people and settle more easily into a new life. This helps to alleviate homesickness and improves their effectiveness in the workplace or place of learning.

A safe and comfortable home life makes for a happier Melbourne experience.

Typical Tenant Profiles

Flexi (Hidden by Airbnb) is open to a wide range of people from professional backgrounds usually between (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) years of age. Typical residents are overseas, inter and intrastate visitors, corporate and career professionals, academics, post and undergraduates (3rd year and over), trainees, language students, doctors, nurses, teachers and other specialists or people in the throes of re-establishing a home and life in Melbourne.

Ben and I hope you choose to stay with us and we have the opportunity to make your stay in Melbourne a life long happy memory.

name: Quiet Neighbourhood.  Close to everything!
summary: This is a quiet neighbourhood with a great little oasis locked inside its grounds.  It's also so close to the action of the CBD that you will scarcely believe it!
space: Welcome to Melbourne, one of the truly great cities of the world, regardless of the season.  Sometimes we get the pleasure of seeing all four seasons in a day! Before I go into depth with my description, I will list the Pros and Cons (or FAQ) of the place based on the feedback I’ve received from guests over the last 3-4 years.  These are all listed in the main features but are sometimes missed by guests. PROS Location – Close to the city but not too close.  It’s in a quiet street opposite a block that is only occupied during business hours yet it’s only a 10-15 minute walk to the CBD and less than 10 minutes via tram.  It’s even closer to Melbourne icons such as the Shrine of Remembrance, Botanical Gardens, NGV and the Arts Centre. Proximity to Public Transport – A 2 minute walk to the nearest stop where 8 different tram lines will take you towards the CBD meaning you will rarely wait more than 2-3 minutes.  Trams heading in the opposite direction will take you to places such as St Kil
host_about:
I'm a 38 year old male. I work in the restaurant industry so work long and unusual hours although I have recently switched to Mon-Fri days :-) but I am always respectful of noise levels when arriving home late. I lead an active life outside of work with sports, exercise and socialising keeping me busy. I am friendly, relaxed and will happily do what I can to help you enjoy your time in the greatest city in the world.  Having an inside knowledge of where to eat and drink is a definite advantage to guests who stay with me!  As an ex chef, you may get the odd home cooked meal as well!

My love of sport will give you an insight into which is the best game on any given weekend to attend.   I grew up in the country originally and have travelled extensively having lived overseas for over 3 years.  I understand the ups and downs of travel but also remember some of my most memorable experiences coming about because I 'met a local'

summary: Privacy, privacy and more privacy! You enter by a remote control garage to your own door into a 3 bedroom apartment. You have total privacy, living room with leather couch & tv. We love guests to use the BBQ & sit on the deck with a glass of wine, or visit our veggie patch & sample the veggies.
space: People wanting a rural experience close to the city! We have farm animals, you can go yabbying in our dam, many country walks and enjoy rambling through vegetable gardens with lots of bush settings. Come & relax and enjoy the serenity!
host_about:
Hi 
My name is Lynne. I’m retired and live an active life with my husband, Jeff. 
We both had very busy careers and now it’s our time to live life to the full. 
We enjoy meeting new people with Airbnb. 
I’m a retired primary school principal who worked in the educational sector for over 36 years. I love travelling to new places. One of my favourite places is South Africa where I fell in love with elephants. I want to save them all from poachers, hunters and people breaking their spirits for the tourist industry. Just a dream but need to have hope! 
I love gardening and spend many happy hours working in about 2 acres of gardens. 

Enjoy meeting our guests and many a wine has been enjoyed together on our deck! 

Now guests are having their wedding photos taken by the dam under the gum trees with the ducks, next to the dry creek bed, also by sculptures and arches in our gardens. The Lemon Scented Gums on our driveway provide a beautiful backdrop too.

Wedding packages now in progress to be married here, stay here on Wedding night and catch up for family celebration the next day on the deck.  Love this idea.

host_about:
Hi, my name is Valeria. My husband Ben and I own and manage a number of upmarket guesthouses located in the inner Melbourne suburbs. 

We specialise in offering a new and unique opportunity to overseas, inter and intrastate visitors, career professionals, academics, post and undergraduates (3rd year and over), trainees, language students, doctors, teachers and other business specialists to gain superior inner Melbourne accommodation and lessen the stresses of moving to a new town, new state or a new country.

We offer fully furnished, centrally located properties with plenty of parking and quality fixtures and furnishings, each has an alfresco entertainment area and BBQ in a garden setting, a fully equipped property in an exclusive professional apartment house environment, where new arrivals, to Melbourne, or people going through a lifestyle transition, can experience an instant community atmosphere for medium (from two weeks), or long term stays, and say goodbye to lonely, restrictive and expensive apartment living.

No more solitary TV dinners! Each property provides apartment house accommodation on a room-by-room basis with shared kitchen, dining and lounge facilities. This style of apartment house living provides opportunities for new arrivals, to Melbourne to quickly, form friendships, build networks with other likeminded people and settle more easily into a new life. This helps to alleviate homesickness and improves their effectiveness in the workplace or place of learning.

A safe and comfortable home life makes for a happier Melbourne experience.

Typical Tenant Profiles

Flexi (Hidden by Airbnb) is open to a wide range of people from professional backgrounds usually between (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) years of age. Typical residents are overseas, inter and intrastate visitors, corporate and career professionals, academics, post and undergraduates (3rd year and over), trainees, language students, doctors, nurses, teachers and other specialists or people in the throes of re-establishing a home and life in Melbourne.

Ben and I hope you choose to stay with us and we have the opportunity to make your stay in Melbourne a life long happy memory.

host_about:
A few years ago, I was working a corporate job that constantly drained me. I spent most days browsing the web on places that I would love to visit. Before I knew it, I was consumed by wanderlust. At that moment, I quit my job and decided to travel in order to discover myself and the wonders that the world has to offer.

I've since become an avid traveller that has journeyed across the globe. Meeting new people, discovering new foods, embracing new cultures - it's something I'd never get sick of. 

Through these experiences, I wish to emulate the Airbnb hosts I stayed with during my own travels and give back by providing a place to stay in the beautiful city that I call Melbourne - and home. 

I'll do my utmost best to meet all my guests. And when I do, I always welcome them with my signature high-five!

name: LUXICO - White Lodge
summary: Fusing high-end inner-Melbourne living with the restful and luxurious elements of boutique hotel design, White Lodge is a breathtaking, large contemporary home where time simply stands still.  Lazing around the pool, waking up to a leafy outlook and settling in for an al fresco meal; they’re all just a small part of what makes this four-bedroom home an exceptional getaway. space: Brimming with luxurious appeal, White Lodge will wow you with its contemporary façade and modernist elements.  And the allure of this home continues with the elevated, yet private pool that takes centre-stage at the front of the property.  You’ll want to dive in before even setting foot inside, or at least get close to the action and relax on the deck chairs.  Inside the appeal escalates with an expansive split-level floor plan, impressive architectural features, a crisp white palette and sophisticated furniture. With two living rooms to retreat to, you’re assured complete comfort and elegance.  From the light-filled front living area with its white linen sofas and views of the garden and pool, to the more casual living space at the rear of the home with its feature skylight and generous views of the garden; you’ll find the perfect atmosphere whatever your mood.  And if you crave more space to spread out and enjoy the garden views, you’ll find that in the kitchen and dining zone.  The
host_about:
Why stay in a hotel when you can enjoy the space and amenity of a designer home?

Luxico manages designer and luxury homes across Melbourne, Sydney, Palm Beach, Byron Bay, Noosa and the Mornington Peninsula with many new locations coming in 2018.

All Luxico homes are  fully equipped with 5-star linens, towels, luxury toiletries, gourmet welcome hampers, free Wi-Fi and all the essential items that you will require during your stay.

Luxico's Housekeeping and Concierge Services teams are on hand to assist with airport transfers, grocery deliveries, catering, extra cleaning and anything else you might require.

Guests travelling with children can request toys, activities, travel cots and high chairs, whilst pet owners have a number of great properties to choose from with doggy beds, water bowls and other items provided to minimize your luggage.

You have a free tram stop on your doorstep and Melbourne's largest train station across the street. Melbourne is Australia’s most exciting and rapidly developing city! So there is often construction around the city-centre which can be a little bit noisy for some people at times. However, the food, the sights, the vibe and the friendly people more than make up for any construction noise :)
space: To stay in theme with the airbnb culture, I aim to be 100% open, honest and transparent with all guests. My studio apartment is not a 6 star penthouse, nor is it a 1 star budget motel either. Its somewhere in between. My cozy little studio is clean, neat, basic and comfortable with some 5 star touches like hair dryer, hair straighter, unique artwork and breathtaking, panoramic views from the rooftop pool. What makes it attractive is its prime location and simplicity. If you’re looking for super fancy accommodation on the high end, or perhaps something super cheap on the low-end, then my place is probably not for you. But if you’re looking for accommodation that is decent, basic, clean, neat and comfortable with a few stylish perks and surprises, then my apartment is definitely for you. Unbeatable location and breathtaking ocean and city views from the rooftop pool make this place a unique and authentic Melbourne experience.

It says I should write what I can't live without so here goes: good food, nice wine and my mobile phone.  I love Jazz, soul, r&b and blues music the most.  Love watching movies, tennis, netball, generally any sport and like beach locations more than the snow.

space: The guest bedroom is blanketed by warm rays of the sun in the day, and it overlooks a beautiful, old, rustic building across the road. The view opens up to the sky, where you can enjoy beautiful sunrises and sunsets everyday. Little touches in the room makes it warmer and friendlier - candles for a homemade aromatherapy and flowers to brighten up the day. - Nate

host_about:
Why stay in a hotel when you can enjoy the space and amenity of a designer home?

Luxico manages designer and luxury homes across Melbourne, Sydney, Palm Beach, Byron Bay, Noosa and the Mornington Peninsula with many new locations coming in 2018.

All Luxico homes are  fully equipped with 5-star linens, towels, luxury toiletries, gourmet welcome hampers, free Wi-Fi and all the essential items that you will require during your stay.

Luxico's Housekeeping and Concierge Services teams are on hand to assist with airport transfers, grocery deliveries, catering, extra cleaning and anything else you might require.

Guests travelling with children can request toys, activities, travel cots and high chairs, whilst pet owners have a number of great properties to choose from with doggy beds, water bowls and other items provided to minimize your luggage.

name: Southbank Corporate 1BDR Apartment with Views
summary: Brand new apartment close to the CBD and transport, featuring spacious interior, comfy bed and fast WIFI
space: Overview Brand new apartment in close proximity to the city with stylish design and complete set of amenities for you to cook, relax or enjoy depending on your stay requirements. For the busy business traveller, getting around on foot is ideal, otherwise trams are on Clarendon St that can take you to Southern Cross Station, the Exhibition Centre as Crown Casino. Neighbourhood Southbank is an excellent location to experience all the best parts of Melbourne without being right in the city centre. Walk up Clarendon St and the Exhibition Centre is on the left and Crown Casino on the right then cross the bridge and you're in the city at Southern Cross Station. Getting Around Walking is super easy and you can get to Southern Cross Station in about 10 mins, or there is a tram stop at the corner of City Rd and Clarendon St if you've got a few bags to carry and you can get anywhere once you're over the bridge in the CBD.
host_about:
I'm Linton, I own and run a short-stay management company, Beyond a Room, here in Melbourne. If you book with me you'll be communicating with both myself and my staff.

I’m an entrepreneur, architecture graduate, photographer, cyclist (NOT the lycra kind), volunteer, adventurer and problem solver.

During my studies I worked at various cafes and architecture offices to save up for shoestring trips around the world. My grandma once told me I had ‘champagne taste but a beer budget’ and it’s a motto I’ve enjoyed applying to different parts of my life to get the more out of less and find enjoyment in the little things.

I love discovering authentic experiences when I travel and I love being able to share the opportunity with others, to live like a local when they travel too.

Some of my most memorable trips have been couch-surfin across Russia while taking the Trans Siberian, living in Helsinki and learning to hand build furniture, riding a vintage steel bicycle through France to race in L’Eroica and buying a car on craigzlist in Los Angeles and driving across the south, east and north coasts to arrive in Vancouver.

My listings are all managed by Beyond a Room and are all given names that I think reflect the character of the property and area. My aim is to give guests a unique and local perspective on the location and share my knowledge and experience of this wonderful city with travellers so that they feel at home. Search Beyond a Room to find out more about how we can help manage your airbnb.

I try to keep all my calendars up to date so if it’s available in the calendar, you can usually just go ahead and book

host_about:
Hi from Bronnie and Neil ;-)
We love being airbnb hosts and sharing our homes and our beautiful city with others.
We have been airbnb hosts for over four years and during that time we have met amazing and wonderful people from all around Australia and all parts of the world.
We started with the spare room in our own home and now have 20 properties, from high end luxury to family friendly apartments that we offer our guests. We even have a 7 bedroom, 7 bathroom mansion near the sea in St Kilda for larger groups! 
We use airbnb ourselves whenever we travel and feel we know what people are looking for. Good value, great locations, clean, comfortable and friendly! All our properties are in great locations, are professionally cleaned and we use hotel quality, commercially laundered linen on comfortable beds.  We meet all our guests on arrival to say hello and are on hand to offer help, advice and inside tips of places to go and things to see. 
Most of our properties include free parking which is a real bonus in the city and Foxtel (cable) television and other homely touches so you 'can live like a local'. (You can view our properties by clicking the View Full Profile link below and clicking on the listings on the left hand side of the page). 

A little bit about ourselves ... we're pretty easy going, and love getting out and about exploring different places. We are both keen travellers and have done our fair share of it in Australia and overseas - whether backpacking, camping, or an occasional splurge on 5-star resorts! You wouldn't call us 'party animals', but we do like socialising and meeting people.  We enjoy a wide variety of interests, love the movies, eating out, popping down to the beach on our scooter or pushbikes, and enjoying the many exciting sporting events and festivals that Melbourne has to offer.
Our motto is "strangers are just friends you haven't met yet!"
Wishing you happy travels and looking forward to meeting you soon :-)

Best regards
Bronnie and Neil

You're also close to some of Melbourne's best food and nightlife districts including Brunswick St, Fitzroy, and the laneway bars of the CBD. host_about: I'm very lucky and grateful to live in a fabulous city, to have a wonderful partner, a beautiful family and great friends.  I have many beautiful, gorgeous children in my life but don't have any myself.  I'm proud and privileged to own Wyndham Cottage and I'm enjoying the challenge of making it a perfect place to stay and loving hosting my guests and getting to meet new travelers or people just on holiday locally, they are always happy and its great energy to engage with people on or organising a holiday.  I'm most content when spending time with my girlfriend, whether we are on an adventure and seeing something new for the first time and laughing or meeting some new people, or even if we are just taking it easy at dinner together.  I'm fascinated with simply listening to people I meet along life's journey but I'm also very engaged when investigating something new or a little different.  To hear and see how others interpret our world and find ways to enjoy it amazes and inspires me.  I'm a bit of a perfectionist who thrives on a challenge and I think in life the opportunity we have to give and share is a blessing - nothing makes me happier on an individual level.   I think all these factors combine well and make me a great person to book (Website hidden by Airbnb) least I hope they do because I always want my guests to leave the cottage smiling, although maybe a little sad to leave, but to reflect on how perfect their stay was, on holiday we all deserve to feel special.

My husband, Bill and I have been in the furnished accommodation business since June 2006. 

Our company is Apartment Stays Melbourne.

We offer quality fully furnished, centrally located and affordable apartments for short or long stays in Melbourne. Our apartments offer residential and corporate living solutions with savings of up to 60% on hotel stays.

The apartments are situated in the lively and dynamic suburbs of South Yarra and East Melbourne/CBD. 

All of our apartments are within 200metres of a tram AND train stop and in close proximity to other public transport, a range of major shopping precincts and multiple dining and entertainment choices in the pulsating heart of Melbourne’s cosmopolitan districts.

Apartment Stays Melbourne provides a number of different furnished apartment configurations to suit all needs and are therefore ideally suited for the business traveller, academics, students, doctors, teachers, other professionals, long term travellers and families.

We hope that you will choose to stay with us during your time in Melbourne. Our promise to you is that we will help make your time here a life long pleasurable and rich experience.

I enjoy going for walks or riding my bike along our beautiful river, park and beach-side tracks; I do yoga, meditate, paint and dance latin (all with varying degrees of success :) I also like attending live music events, theatres, galleries, eating out and meeting great people, all of which I can enjoy in this great city of ours. host_about:
Hi there,

Welcome to St Kilda!  Myself and my husband Glen started our AIrbnb journey when we were a newly married couple that had just returned from our honeymoon in Africa. 

Now, fast forward 4 years on, we have 2 girls under two, but still look back fondly on our years of international travel, and hope that we can show our family the world one day.

We would love to give you the opportunity to stay in our apartment, and enjoy travelling through Melbourne, the way we have travelled through many parts of the world.

Both my husband and I are professionally employed (Occupational Therapist & Project Manager) and  work in Melbourne.  We lived in our apartment in St Kilda for many years, however as our family has expanded, we are now based on the Mornington Peninsula, and pop in to stay in our apartment in St Kilda every now and then.

We consider ourselves to be excellent houseguests, and we often have friends stay over - we love hosting. We are  neat, clean and considerate. We are also non smokers and we  like to keep fit.

That's us in a nutshell - please feel free to contact us if you have any questions.

host_about:
I have been described as Talkative, inquisitive and slightly nocturnal. I know I am incredibly curious, and become very passionate, motivated and excited over subjects and projects that catch my interest. I love talking about abstract ideas and philosophies, and like nothing more than picking these things apart - and working out how they apply and work in the world. This is partly what makes me nocturnal - once I've started doing something, learning something or talking about something I want to draw conclusions from it and work it totally out.

I studied nanotechnology and physics at uni, and work as a project manager - I really want to know the answer to everything! And although I am a long way off that point, when I am most happy when solving problems, dealing with issues or delivering my knowledge to others. My nightmare is not having something to work out or work towards - I go almost mad with boredom.

host_about: I absolutely love going from one adventure to the next. Road trips are my favourite, together with a mixtape and a good supply of junk food. name: Northside in Preston + wifi
summary: Cute 2 bedroom unit in the north side of Melbourne.  25 mins from Airport
space: Hi I'm Kirsten. I am an artist and instructional designer living in vibrant Preston with my lagotto puppy called Funf. My 2 bedroom unit is on a quiet street just off the Gilbert Road Tram 11 which takes 35 mins into the city. My unit has got central heating, has lots of natural light and is situated on a quiet street that is a 5 mins walk to tram stop 45 on Gilbert Road. My house is a 4 minute walk to Woolworths Coburg Hill on Elizabeth Street. I am a 15 min walk to Preston market open Wednesdays to Saturdays, great fresh produce and atmosphere. I love walking there on a Saturday and cooking afterwards. My unit is decorated eclectically with artwork. I enjoy making art, going to galleries, yoga and meditation. I have done lots of travel myself and am keen to meet like minded individuals who are keen to explore the wonders of my favourite city, Melbourne. I have travelled to South East Asia, Africa, USA, Europe and lived in Japan. I have lots of international friends who I have hosted

Hi I'm Kirsten. I am an artist and designer living in vibrant Preston. I have a young lagotto dog called Fünf. My 2 bedroom unit is on a quiet street just off the Gilbert Road Tram 11 which takes 35 -45 mins into the city. I am a 15 min walk to Preston market open Wednesdays to Saturdays, great fresh produce and atmosphere. I love walking there on a Saturday and cooking afterwards. My unit is decorated eclectically with artwork. I enjoy making ceramics, walking my dog, going to galleries and yoga.

I have done lots of travel myself and am keen to meet like minded individuals who are keen to explore the wonders of my favourite city, Melbourne. I have travelled to South East Asia,  Africa, USA, Europe, South America and lived in Japan. I have lots of international friends who i have hosted and I've got plenty of ideas of what to do and see here. 
I am about a 25 min Uber  from the airport which is about $36. Also a 12 min walk to Preston station. Merri Creek, Coburg Trash and Treasure Market, local cafes and yoga studios are short walks away. I love making ceramics, sculpture and jewellery from my home studio. I also love music and am a short tram ride to Northcote Social Club or Brunswick Street, Fitzroy.

host_about:
My name is Lyn, I started doing Airbnb June 2017.I would read news on the internet just to catch up with the rest of the world. That's how I knew Airbnb. I love music, movies, and meeting people from different places, listening their stories. My life motto is 'to travel is to live.'

A travel lover myself, I love to host people wherever I am in the world. 

I met with travellers around the world. Every body was so polite and friendly. When I talk to them I can feel the excitement and happiness. It's totally different compare to what I thought people are like. Maybe because this communicate is great, I don't know. Then I thought "I want to be people like my guests". I want people around me to feel life is great and there are a lot to look forward to. The guests really gave me a lot motivation towards my work and my life. Here I have to thank you all.

name: Mountain retreat, family friendly cottage
summary: Hill ‘n’ Dale is nestled on 54 acres of mountain forest and tucked away in the Yarra Valley hills. We are only 1.5 hours from Melbourne, 20 minutes from Healesville Sanctuary, right on the doorstep of the Yarra Valley winery region.
space: Our beautiful property is forested with stringy bark eucalyptus trees, mountain ash trees and tree ferns. The natural environment attracts an abundance of Australian wildlife including wombats, wallabies, king parrots, black/silver crested cockatoos, and lyrebirds. We enjoy fresh mountain spring water and clean country air. We are a farm property with over 600 organic hazelnut trees, several chestnut trees, various kitchen garden veggie and berry patches. In house shiatsu massage treatments are also available at the farm property to help you fully relax and unwind. Shiatsu is a dynamic body therapy which draws on Traditional Chinese Medicine. Each treatment is uniquely designed to meet your needs, leaving you more aligned, restored and centered in your body.
host_about:
Hi there. We are a young family who love connecting with nature, people and food. Our passion is to grow great food, be as self-sustaining (as possible!), and create a nourishing space to share with others. Phuong is a shiatsu practitioner, keen gardener and loves cooking. Eddy manages the farm/cottages and loves building from recycled goods. 
We are fortunate enough to call our 54 acres of incredible rainforest and farm bush our home, and hope you enjoy our hideaway as much as we do!

This apartment is our home, so we would be looking for respectful guests who are looking to get some privacy away from the busy backpacker hostels. We will be away on holiday and would love for guests to enjoy the luxury of a private apartment while not breaking the bank. The apartment is not the newest due to the fact that it's part of a historic building, but it definitely has charm and character.

summary: * Sunshine streams through the cathedral ceilings * Rear of the house opens into an enchanting cottage garden * A short walk to the river and beautiful parklands
space: A Victorian terrace with period charm and modern convenience. Enhanced by natural light, period features, high ceilings with ceiling roses, wide skirting, panelled doors and open fire places. It includes an arched hallway, 1 bedroom, living room, well appointed galley style kitchen opening to family room, and bathroom with unique sunken bath. A pretty rear garden ideal for outdoor living. The rear section of the house was designed by architect A. Cronin and completed in 1983. It is a timeless fresh, light filled design with cathedral ceilings and windows a plenty. It looks current and contemporary. It is a very long skinny house that I lovingly refer to it as "the pencil."
