space: Unknown
host_about:
We are a couple of young professionals from Italy and Mauritius and have been living in Melbourne for the past 9 years. Our shared passions include: 

Travelling: We absolutely love it and look out for every opportunity to experience new cultures, landscapes and adventures around the world - we have been in more than 30 countries to date and planning to visit a lot more. We speak English, French, Italian and Spanish between the two of us.

Food: Along with travelling, food is another thing we love. We fancy adventuring ourselves in the variety of great diners scattered around Melbourne as well as experiencing different cuisines when travelling.

Cycling/Yoga: One thing that Valerie cannot live without is yoga! Every opportunity is good to roll the mat and practice. I (Davide) love cycling especially very long rides +150km and cycling in the mountains! I cycled the Australian Alps and seek to experience steep up and downhills around the world further. Find me on Strava (Dave March) if you are into cycling.

Our motto in life is 'Carpe Diem' (seize the day - and enjoy every moment of it!) 

We would love to have you here to share our experiences and show you around the hidden gems of Melbourne!

We have compost bins downstairs, recycling, a bike you can borrow & an awesome bulk food store nearby, so this is the perfect home-away-from-home for an environmentalist abroad! 5min walk to Balaclava station & all the excellent cafes of Carlisle St. Easy 15min train to CBD.
space: The building has good insulation so stays fairly cool in summer and warm in winter without central air-conditioning. You'll find a fan and a heater in your room that you are of course welcome to use if you need to. All windows have fly screens, which means you will have a peaceful, mosquito-free sleep on warmer nights.  There is a balcony too which gets a nice view of the sunset and also has a BBQ which you're more than welcome to use, I only ask that you remember to turn off the gas when done.  The apartment is on the second floor meaning that there are some stairs, but I am more than happy to help you with any luggage up the stairs.

Aside from my native tongue, hablo español, Eλληνικά, un peu du français (mal), un poco italiano, deutsch, základní české and basically pick up as much as I can in whichever city I find myself in. I am the kind of traveller who prefers to stay and get to know a place rather than visit as a tourist, and I believe the best way to do so is to stay longer, walk slower, and talk to as many people as possible (and be safe).

summary: Perch on a wooden tractor-seat stool and eat breakfast in an open space where industrial chic merges with modern kitchen design. Exposed brick walls are among the original details still visible in this apartment in a reconfigured Victorian school.
space: Sun-filled and charming, with the kind of design elements and attention to detail to make you smile, our one bedroom apartment Vera will surely charm you. With everything to make your stay as comfortable as home including an incredible, fully-equipped kitchen with the added feature of an espresso machine for a morning brew. The lounge area includes a stereo and internet-enabled TV; the lovely bathroom has a shower, bathtub and hairdyer (I supply hotel quality towels); the place is baby friendly with porta-cot and a highchair; the laundry has a washer,dryer, iron and ironing board. The property also features the all-important WiFi, Split system Air-conditioning and a beautiful courtyard!
host_about:
I'm Linton, I own and run a short-stay management company, Beyond a Room, here in Melbourne. If you book with me you'll be communicating with both myself and my staff.

I’m an entrepreneur, architecture graduate, photographer, cyclist (NOT the lycra kind), volunteer, adventurer and problem solver.

During my studies I worked at various cafes and architecture offices to save up for shoestring trips around the world. My grandma once told me I had ‘champagne taste but a beer budget’ and it’s a motto I’ve enjoyed applying to different parts of my life to get the more out of less and find enjoyment in the little things.

I love discovering authentic experiences when I travel and I love being able to share the opportunity with others, to live like a local when they travel too.

Some of my most memorable trips have been couch-surfin across Russia while taking the Trans Siberian, living in Helsinki and learning to hand build furniture, riding a vintage steel bicycle through France to race in L’Eroica and buying a car on craigzlist in Los Angeles and driving across the south, east and north coasts to arrive in Vancouver.

My listings are all managed by Beyond a Room and are all given names that I think reflect the character of the property and area. My aim is to give guests a unique and local perspective on the location and share my knowledge and experience of this wonderful city with travellers so that they feel at home. Search Beyond a Room to find out more about how we can help manage your airbnb.

I try to keep all my calendars up to date so if it’s available in the calendar, you can usually just go ahead and book

name: Best of Brunswick on a Budget!
summary: Live like a local, with locals!  We have a bright and light private room in our friendly and creative share house, situated in Melbourne's vibrant inner north.  If you fancy good coffee, small bars, food trucks, live music and vintage shopping, then East Brunswick is for you!  You can safely stroll or cycle the inner north (Brunswick, Fitzroy, Carlton) or take a 15 minute tram to the city, before escaping back to the refuge of your peaceful room. LGBTIQ friendly please!
space: About us: We are four creatives aged between 30 and 41 hailing from Australia, Colombia and Brazil and we have lived communally with one another for a substantial time, in a warm and mature home. This is definitely not a hostel or rooming house situation!  We live in a lovely old Californian bungalow in the leafy heart of diverse Brunswick. We have a large backyard and thriving edible garden and we are happy to welcome you into our happy, well-functioning share house!  The room: There is a choice of two rooms depending on which one of us is away from home for study, work or travel. Both rooms have small double and or queen-sized beds and include wardrobes, dressing tables and desks. We also offer heating and fans to suit the season and clean towels and linen are assured. Hair care / body wash essentials are also provided.  Communal spaces: we have a large backyard that is half paved and half vegetable garden. There is an outdoor setting for use and you are welcome to eat from the garde
host_about:
I'm a nature-loving, novel-reading, coffee-appreciating, visual-arting, social justice-minded, vegan office worker! 

Relaxed and respectful, with a long history of happy share housing. 

I look forward to connecting and sharing!
